title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add corn, flour and seasonings.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, then baking powder.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot grease.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet, breaking meat apart with a fork.
Pour fat off as it collects (important).
Stir in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Bring to a boil; cover pan. Simmer, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Cook until macaroni is tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Blend in sour cream.
Reheat just to boiling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot butter rum
directions: Heat butter (real hot); add powdered sugar, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar.
When lumps are all gone, add ice cream that has been cut into quarters.
Stir until melted.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir milk into mixture with a fork.
Do not overmix. Drop from spoon on greased baking sheet.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and bananas thoroughly.
Sift flour.
Add soda and baking powder and sift again.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and broken nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or longer.

title: muesli
directions: Mix ingredients.
If used for back packing and hiking, only need to add water.
Add milk when used as cereal.

title: creamed chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine until tender. Stir in soup, sour cream, parsley, sherry and paprika.
Add chicken meat; stir often.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
In large bowl, alternate layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Continue until all pudding is used. Chill to set.

title: sugar-free cantaloupe delight
directions: Mix yogurt, sweetener and extract.
Blend in fruit and chill before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter in double boiler.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bars in double boiler.
Swirl into other mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well and store, covered, in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Do not freeze.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Pour batter into greased muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Bake for 15-20 minutes. Serve warm.
The batter will keep in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: super biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread ring
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into 12 cup Bundt cake pan, well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower cheese casserole
directions: Mix cheese, soup and rice in a 3-quart casserole dish; fold in broccoli and cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped oyster casserole
directions: Combine all of the crumbs and butter.
Alternate layers of oysters and crumb mixture. Sprinkle each with seasoning.
Pour the oyster liquor and milk over this. Top with crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: grandma's refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust and bake in a spring-form pan; cool crust.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and dried beans
directions: Place ham in large pot and cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Dice celery, carrots and onion.
Dice potatoes.
Add to meat.
Add dried beans that have been soaked for about 2 hours. Also, add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook all together until potatoes are done.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix all together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pie.

title: miriam's sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage until brown, then drain.
Bake crust at 400° for 5 minutes.
Punch holes in it.
Place sausage in crust.
Add grated cheese and onion.
Beat eggs, salt, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes and
at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Make 3 days ahead.
Shave about 1 tablespoon loosely in glass. Add 7-Up or similar drink.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips; pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Stir until well coated. Put in a paper sack with the powdered sugar and shake until well coated.

title: black and white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, cocoa and cream.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Cool to room temperature.
Add butter or butter substitute and flavoring.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into well buttered pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 x 7 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients until blended.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: manicotti dough and cheese filling
directions: Beat ingredients for dough until smooth.
Let stand 1/2 hour or longer.
Heat 8-inch Teflon skillet, pour in 3 tablespoons of batter, turn pan to cover bottom and fry until done (do not turn over).
Cool on wire rack, stack cooked cakes between wax paper. Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets; set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Remove jackets from potatoes, slice or cube and mix with dressing mixture.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: helen's rolls
directions: Melt shortening and sugar in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast mixture.
Add salt and beaten egg; then enough flour to make stiff.
Store in refrigerator until about 2 hours before baking time.
Roll out, cut and let rise until double.
Bake at 450°.

title: baked nacho dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice off top of bread and set aside. Pull out center of bread, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Cut top of loaf and center into 1-inch cubes for dipping.
Place bread shell on baking sheet.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, cream cheese, crab and onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour mixture into bread shell. Cover loosely with foil. Bake 20 minutes or until bread is warm. Remove foil. Serve with bread cubes for dipping. Add crumbled bacon to garnish.

title: angel food cake with chocolate flavored whipped cream
directions: Slice cake into three layers.
Combine whipped cream, sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Spread on each layer to make a three layered cake; use all the topping and sprinkle the sliced almonds on the top.
Refrigerate before serving.
Delicious.

title: chocolate cherry brownies
directions: Blend together cake mixture (no mixer needed).
Bake on 350° for 25-30 minutes (ovens vary).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add sauce, chilies, cumin, salt and red pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Layer in buttered 9-inch square baking dish half of the following: tortilla chips, Monterey Jack cheese, beef and sauce.
Repeat once.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: best banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Add milk, lemon juice and then the flour to the creamed mixture.
Then add soda, salt, baking powder, bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour in 2 loaf pans well-greased and floured.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
In a bowl, lightly beat eggs and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
Shake a few pieces in bag and coat well.
In a skillet, heat 1/4-inch of oil to 350°.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Reduce heat and cook until done.

title: wholesome johnnycakes
directions: Mix dry goods in bowl.
Separate eggs and whip egg whites in a separate bowl until stiff.
Set aside.
Add milk, oil and egg yolks to dry goods and mix thoroughly.
Batter consistency should be similar to a cake batter; if not, add more milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook on lightly oiled or sprayed griddle on low to medium heat.
Serve with favorite syrup or honey.

title: gorton (french) *(pork pate)
directions: Cook pork butts and onions in water to cover.
Mash.
Low boil.
Check and mash.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add cloves and cinnamon.
Let cool a little.
Add milk and mix.
Put in containers, and chill.
Spread on toast.

title: chicken and crescent almondine
directions: Combine chicken, soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, mayonnaise, celery, onion and sour cream; heat.
Pour into ungreased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Separate crescents into 2 rectangles and place over mixture.
Sprinkle cheese, almonds and oleo over rolls.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add oil, sugar and zucchini, which should be peeled if old.
Add vanilla, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Cool in pans.

title: brownie drops
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Stir.
Cool.
Beat eggs until foamy, then add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until thickened (5 minutes on electric mixer).
Blend in chocolate.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; blend.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until cookies feel "set" when very lightly touched, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: ham and potato pie(main dish)
directions: Peel potatoes, sliced very thin, covered with cold water. Make pie crust mix.
Follow directions on package.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Stir until mixture forms a ball.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch.
Cut in rectangles 1 x 3-inches.
Gently fry in 1/2-inch hot oil, lightly pressing down until dough becomes firm.
Turn and brown.
Drain. Serve hot with honey.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Mix beef, oatmeal, onion, egg, spices and milk.
Shape into small meatballs; brown in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Mix cornstarch and sugar; stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple and meatballs.
Heat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put all but onion rings into large bowl and beat on high until light and fluffy.
Spoon into greased baking pan.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and then cut into bars.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Use a 12 x 14-inch pan.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight for 4 to 6 hours. Drain beans, rinse and place in large pot.
Cover with water and add diced salt pork. Cook 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Simmer until beans are tender, a couple of hours.
May have to add water throughout cooking period.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in a double boiler.
Pour in Rice Chex, raisins and peanuts and mix well. While still warm, pour into garbage bag with 10x sugar.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and let stand. Combine sugar, flour and milk in a small saucepan. Over medium heat let boil and thicken while constantly stirring. Remove from heat, stir in gelatin and let cool. Add whip cream, vanilla and almond extract. Mix well and pour into a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: baked steak
directions: Heat over to 350 degrees. Trim meat, cut into serving sized pieces. Pound to 1/2 inch thick with meat mallet. On a sheet of waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper. Dip steak in flour mixture, turn to coat.

title: noodle surprise
directions: Fry hamburger; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, water, tomato paste, garlic powder, oregano, sweet basil, salt and sugar; simmer.
Mix sour cream, yogurt and scallions with cooked noodles. In a serving dish, layer hamburger mixture, then noodle mixture. Top with cheese.

title: no mess pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Divided in half.
Place between wax paper and roll out.

title: chili
directions: Dice onion; brown meat.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve with cheese and crackers.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Combine milk and onion in small mixing bowl.
Mix well and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, cheese, butter and milk mixture. Stir only to moisten.
Spread batter evenly in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 15 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Mix baking soda with soup and add to shortening mixture.
Sift flour, cinnamon and cloves. Add to mixture.
Mix well. Add raisins. Spoon into medium loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn oven off and let pudding remain in oven for 1/2 hour longer.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Over medium heat, add garlic, salt, pepper, chili powder and masa.
Mix until fat is absorbed.
Slowly add hot water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring often.
Serve with Mexican cornbread or crackers. Top with grated cheese, if desired.
This serves a large crowd and freezes well.

title: strawberry delight congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat liquid; dissolve jello in the hot liquid.
Add all ingredients except sour cream.
Divide into 2 parts.
Congeal 1 part until firm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well; leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: spinach sandwiches
directions: Cook and drain spinach; cool.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 13 full size sandwiches. These keep well in refrigerator 2 to 3 days if put in airtight container with barely damp paper towel.
This recipe is one that is never left over at dinners.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together milk and oil.
Add this to the first 4 ingredients. Pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add fresh or frozen berries.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top of berries, then add water over the top of dough, berries and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll into ball after mixing thoroughly. Crush pecans and roll ball in pecans. Garnish with sliced pimento olives.
Can freeze.

title: mushroom and pepper steak
directions: Coat beef strips in mixture of flour, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. In large skillet, brown meat. Add 1/4 cup Butter. Mix chopped onion, clove of garlic, gravy base, and water; add to meat. Stir. Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours, until meat is tender.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook bacon in a heavy saucepan until browned.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of pan drippings.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Add bacon, broccoli, broth, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Meanwhile, stir cornstarch into a few tablespoons of half and half until blended.
Stir in remaining cream.
Reduce heat to low.
Gradually stir cream mixture into soup.
Stir until mixture boils and thickens, about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut nut topping
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on cake.
Put under broiler until lightly brown.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cut meat and roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in half butter and olive oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in 3 ounces warm Brandy and light.
Put in casserole dish.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Arrange cauliflower in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch; sprinkle with ham. Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth; pour over ham. Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake until topping is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raspberry cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries and drain.
Add sugar and let stand.
Heat 2 cups water to dissolve jello.
Let partially set, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Then add all other ingredients, including cranberries. Cool and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Mix one quart broth with stuffing mix and pour over chicken and soup.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Place drained and cooled macaroni in large bowl.
Pour in dressing and add salad herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well before serving.

title: sands
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Add milk, flour and nuts. Roll small amounts in shape of small finger. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown. Place on wax paper or on something to cool. Roll in powdered sugar. Keep in airtight container.

title: lorraine's cheese wafers
directions: Mix well. Form into small balls and flatten with a fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 8 minutes; remove from heat.
Add the marshmallow cream, white chocolate, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well; pour into greased pans.
Grease pans with margarine.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°; cool.
Mix eggs, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Mix and put on top before baking, if desired.

title: sirloin tips
directions: In a 2 1/2 quart saucepan, saute garlic in hot oil.
Add meat. Brown thoroughly over medium heat.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over a bed of rice.
Serves 4.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place into greased baking dish.
Cover with small amount of gravy made from the broth. Combine the bread cubes, celery, onions, sage, salt and pepper in large skillet, mixing well.
Spread the dressing over the chicken mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until heated through and lightly browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: In kettle on high, mix oleo, sugar and syrup.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove; add vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Bake at 250°, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes.

title: pear crumbleold trees do not bear old fruit
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt. Add egg and stir as well as possible. Add pears and nuts. Some of the juice from the pears will moisten the flour mixture. Place in a greased baking dish. Bake in moderate oven 375° about 45 minutes. The top will be brown. Serve plain or top with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 6 to 8...4 if you like pears.

title: lemon carrots
directions: *Salt is to individual tastes; can omit completely.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Simply add the Ranch dressing mix to 1 pound of ground beef; mix well.
Form into 4 patties; grill or broil until done.
Serves 4.

title: apple latkes
directions: Mix eggs with orange juice, yogurt or milk in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to the egg mixture along with the apples.
Heat a thin layer of oil in a skillet.
Put 1 large tablespoon of batter in pan at a time.
Cook about 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.
Perfect for the holidays.

title: seafoam
directions: In a saucepan, put sugar, water, Karo and salt; boil until 215° on candy thermometer.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff, adding cream of tartar to keep stiff.
When sugar mixture is ready, add egg whites to it and beat for 5 minutes; adding powdered sugar in the first 3 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Set until cold.
Yields 60 to 80 pieces.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Slice onions crosswise. Cut each of the slices in half. Melt butter or margarine in large skillet over medium heat. Cook onions and mushrooms, stirring constantly, until tender. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with 1 cup Crisco. Combine soup, milk and soy sauce. Pour over cheese. Top with bread slices and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese and parsley. Cover and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours. Remove baking dish from the refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 to 20 additional minutes or until thoroughly heated. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices with sugar; add baking powder.
Put oleo in hot potatoes and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; reduce heat to 300° and bake for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Drain all cans.
Pour dressing over veggies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, bell pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise over salad layers.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise.
Bacon bits can be sprinkled on top.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: quickie twists
directions: Mix together nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Pull each biscuit to about 6-inches in length.
Dip in melted margarine, then in sugar mixture.
Twist several times.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 475° for 8 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper, onion and celery for 1 hour or until chicken falls off bone.
Remove bones and dice chicken.
Add potatoes, rice, carrots and bouillon cubes.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut up cheese and add to soup. Heat until cheese melts.

title: 4th of july dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with veggies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon (mixed) on cake batter.
Add the other half of batter and cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Mix together cake mix and crushed pineapple with juice. Spread mixture into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in apple pie filling.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda, stirring just until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Fold in cheese and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until cake tests done.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium bowl combine chicken, 1 cup of cheese, chilies and onion.
In bottom of 3-quart oblong baking dish spread 1/2 can enchilada sauce; set aside.

title: chicken broccoli crescent
directions: Blend cream cheese and soup until smooth.
Stir in chicken, broccoli, onion, salt and pepper.
Unroll 1 can dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press perforations to seal.
Place 1/2 chicken mixture on each rectangle, 1 inch from edge.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over each.
Unroll 2nd dough into 2 rectangles.
Put on top of chicken.
Press perforations and press edges.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 28 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: lasagna bread
directions: Meat Mixture:
In a large frypan, brown meats.
Add all seasonings, onions and paste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In large pan cook onion, celery and water about 20 minutes. Add soup, tuna, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and combine with tuna mixture in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy ham sandwich
directions: Chop onion into small pieces.
Chop green pepper into small pieces; slice fresh mushrooms.
Steam or saute the onion, pepper and mushrooms.
In a large frying pan, add sauce.
Add slices of ham (one at a time) to sauce until all ham is covered in sauce. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german beef rolls
directions: Lay steaks on a flat surface.
Spread each with mustard. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Divide pickles, salt pork (or bacon) and onion among the steaks.
Roll up steaks jelly roll style.
Secure with toothpicks or thread, beef roll clamps.
Heat oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add the steak rolls, brown well on all sides (about 15 minutes).
Pour hot beef broth, peppercorns and bay leaf into pan.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Remove beef rolls.
Discard clamps and arrange on a preheated platter.
Blend cornstarch with a small amount of cold water. Stir into gravy in saucepan and bring to a boil until thick and bubbly.
Serve separately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: For topping, melt the margarine.
Crumble the crackers into melted margarine.
Stir to coat crackers.
Put over chicken mixture and bake in 325° oven until it bubbles.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and Eagle Brand milk.
Then add 1-1/2 quarts milk and vanilla.
Put into ice cream freezer.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Squeeze lemon juice over breasts. Heat oil in pan.
Roll breasts in flour and paprika.
Brown breasts in oil on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and lemon rind, if desired. Sprinkle breasts with sugar and salt.
Add 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Garnish with lemon.

title: korean barbecued beef
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef diagonally across grain into 1/8-inch slices.
(For ease in cutting, partially freeze beef about 1 1/2 hours.)
Mix remaining ingredients; stir in beef until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Drain beef; stir-fry in 10-inch skillet or wok over medium heat until light brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve beef with hot cooked rice, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: imitation crab cake
directions: Squeeze out as much liquid from zucchini as possible; drain on paper towel, the drier the better (keep as close to crab meat consistency as possible).

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, jalapeno and garlic.
Add all ingredients except last four and simmer for 1 hour.
About 20 minutes before serving, saute tortillas and tear into bite-size pieces.
Add to soup.
Put avocado and cheese into individual bowls; pour soup over this. Top with a small dollop of sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mexican hot potatoes
directions: Brown beef with onion. Drain well.
Stir in sour cream, salsa, garlic powder, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over hot baked potatoes.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: nancy's irish german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Cut potatoes into 2 to 3-inch chunks and boil with skins on.
Drain bacon and save the grease.
Chop celery and onions.
Combine both vinegars with bacon drippings; add salt, pepper, celery seed and prepared mustard.
Stir together and simmer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Cook until it comes to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Pour over remaining ingredients while still hot and drop on wax paper.

title: nan's chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of chocolate mixture into eggs.
Add to saucepan of chocolate. Return to heat; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: artichoke heart salad
directions: In a bowl, combine artichokes, olives, green peppers and onions. Add dressing and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Serve with slotted spoon.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Heat and stir together grape jelly, chili sauce and lemon until jelly melts.
Put meat balls into jelly mixture; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in cupcake papers at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: italian cream cheese
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add egg yolks, beating after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour to egg mixture.
Add coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in three 8-inch greased and floured pans in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: strawberry butter
directions: *Or 3 cups fresh berries; they need to be mashed and stand for juice to develop.

title: delta rice
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oleo until soft. Add rice and consomme. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly seven layered salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions. Spread salad dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl. Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon or shredded cheese if desired.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Stir in applesauce and flour.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: turtle bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 1/4 cups warm water.
Stir in 1 cup warm water, sugar, salt, shortening and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Divide into 12 pieces.
Cut off 1/4 of each piece. Form large piece into ball for body.
Place on greased baking pan. From small piece, form head, 4 legs and a tail and place along body.
Insert cloves for eyes.
Make crisscross cuts on back. Cover; let rise until doubled about 30 minutes.
Combine egg and cold water.
Brush over dough.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, sugars, egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by level measuring tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool on baking sheets about 1 minute.
Then place cookies on wire rack to finish cooling.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, peaches and oranges.
Mix together along with jello and cottage cheese.
Fold the mixture into the Cool Whip. Makes a large salad.

title: creamy corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
May be doubled.

title: grinorco(a powerhouse drink)
directions: Mix and serve.
Imbibe only if you are not driving, not walking or have a designated driver.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and stew beef separately until tender.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
In large saucepan, combine chicken, beef and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 45 minutes or until onions are tender.
Best if made the day before.
Freezes well.
Makes 5 to 6 quarts.

title: tasty pastries
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Crumble pie crust into bowl and stir in granulated sugar, egg yolk and yeast mixture. Mix well.
Roll dough into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Make a deep indentation in center of each ball, shaping into shells that are 1 1/2-inches in diameter and 1/4-inch deep.
Spoon 1 teaspoon preserves into each shell. Let rise in warm place for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; put it back in the pot.
Add butter, eggs and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place in buttered pie dish. Spread with spaghetti sauce.
Spread on Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 pies.
This freezes well.

title: seafood boulettes
directions: Place seafood in a large bowl.	Add all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Roll into golf ball size.
Coat balls with additional bread crumbs.
Drop into hot oil and fry until brown.
Makes 50 boulettes.

title: funny cake(a family tradition at christmastime.)
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening until like cornmeal. Sprinkle with cold water. Put dough out on floured board and roll into a 9 or 10-inch crust. Put in pan and flute the edge; set aside.

title: never fail egg custard
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, vanilla, flour, salt, milk and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix and cook the flour and milk until thick and cool.
Mix sugar, Crisco and salt and add to milk mixture.
Beat full 10 minute and add small amounts of powdered sugar while beating. Will cover a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Knife in center should come out clean to test, if done.

title: rich banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Alternate with layers of cookies and bananas in large container.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend together the mayo, sugar and mustard.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Wash and pat dry wings.
Separate wing tips and discard. Deep fry in vegetable oil until golden and crispy, about 15 minutes.
Mix other ingredients in large bowl with lid.
Add cooked wings to sauce.
Coat evenly.
Bake in 200° oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with celery sticks and Ranch or Blue cheese dressing.
Adjust hot sauce to taste.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bring milk to boil and add 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper and grits.
Cook until thick.
Beat 5 minutes with electric beater. Pour into pan; cool and cut into slices and place in casserole like fallen dominoes.
Mix 1/3 cup melted butter and both cheeses and pour over top.
Bake, foil covered, at 400° for 45 minutes and uncover last 5 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candy turtles
directions: Place pecan halves in groups of 4 on a greased cookie sheet. Place 2 Kraft caramels on top of each group.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes or until caramels are softened.
Flatten with a buttered spatula.
Cool.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on waxed paper.
In top of double boiler, melt the chocolate.
Spread over caramel.
Cool until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Do not cook the lasagna noodles. Brown beef, drain fat and add sauce. Cut 6 slices Mozzarella for topping.
Shred remainder and mix with Ricotta, egg, parsley, salt and pepper.
Ladle 1/3 of meat sauce into bottom of baking dish.
Add a layer of 1/3 of the noodles (uncooked) and a layer of 1/3 of the cheeses mixture. Repeat
layers 2 more times and top with Mozzarella slices and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy old fashioned apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch greased cake pan 2/3 full of apples (sliced and peeled).
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1 cup and 2 tablespoons flour, sugar, margarine and egg.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Melt
butter
in a rectangular pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Prepare
cake
according	to directions on box. Pour over
nuts	and coconut.
Melt margarine, mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drizzle over cake (leaving 1-inch from sides).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dumplings for chicken soup
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth or soup.
They only take a few minutes to cook, so don't overcook.

title: meat balls in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine pineapple syrup with chicken broth, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add meat balls, onion and green peppers all to simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Combine and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar; add eggs, vanilla, flour, salt, soda, nuts and quick cooking oats.
Mix well and form into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Cut ham.
Add onions to ham and potatoes.
Cream flour and butter and add to milk when it is warm. Boil until creamy, then add to ham, potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
Place in casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place in ungreased baking dish.
Combine cranberry sauce, onion soup and dressing; mix well.
Pour sauce over chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer or until tender.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Brown pork chops in dish. Put rice and onion soup mix on pork chops and add water. Cover and bake at 375 until done.

title: banana cow(creamy and cool.  kids will love it!)
directions: Combine banana, milk, honey, vanilla and ice in container of electric blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Pour into 2-ounce highball glasses.
Garnish with lime wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put 3/4 crumbs and 1 stick melted butter together and pat into bottom of dish.
Drain asparagus and place on top.
Heat last 4 ingredients until smooth and it makes a sauce.
Pour over asparagus and put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: kiflings
directions: Mix together; roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out and bake until light brown in a 400° oven.
While slightly warm, roll in sifted powdered sugar.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and whipped topping.
Spread on crust. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and place in bottom of an 11 x 7-inch ovenproof casserole.
Cut chicken into large slivers and place on top of broccoli.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix sauce of the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder one hour ahead.
Cook the chicken breasts and pick meat off in pieces.
Cook asparagus or broccoli.
Arrange vegetables in baking dish and place chicken over the asparagus or broccoli.
Pour sauce over and then add cheese, topped with buttered cornflakes crumbs. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except Blue cheese.
Blend well. Gently stir in Blue cheese.
Refrigerate until needed.
Yields 3 cups.
Good as dip for vegetables.

title: taco chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut up in large chunks.
Cook together and simmer 30 minutes the chicken soup, water, Cheez Whiz, onion and peppers.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes longer.
Line casserole dish with Doritos chips. Pour in chicken mixture and top with chips. Cook at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chunky peanut butter bars
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave.
Mix peanut butter and Karo with chocolate and add peanuts.
Add oats, 1 cup at a time, and mix well.
If too stiff, add 1/4 cup boiling water. Spread in an 8 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Cut into squares.

title: robbie's chocolate-walnut bread pudding
directions: Melt bits in 1 cup of milk.
Stir in other two cups of milk; set aside.
Decrust (if desired) and cube bread and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine salt, eggs, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Combine milk and egg mixtures and pour over bread.
Put walnuts (broken or whole) on top.
Set casserole in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
(Check to make sure walnuts don't darken too much.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Cook macaroni in large amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain in colander; rinse in cold water.
Cook ground beef with onions, salt and pepper until meat is brown.
Add cooked macaroni, tomatoes and chili powder.
Turn mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake by directions in 2 (9-inch) round cake pans. When cooked and cooled, slice the 2 layers to make 4. Mix sugar, sour cream and 2 cups of coconut. (Do this night before so sugar will dissolve good.) Refrigerate. This mixture is used to spread between layers. Mix remaining coconut and Cool Whip for top and sides of cake. Refrigerate for 3 or 4 days before eating. The longer it sits, the better the cake.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Using a muffin tin, press one biscuit into each cup, forming a cup with the biscuit.
Brown and drain the ground pork. Stir in the barbecue sauce and spoon the mixture evenly into the cups. Sprinkle the top of the meat with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: rotini antipasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine together cheese, salami, chickpeas, artichokes, vegetables, parsley and onions.
In small bowl, whisk together 13 ounces Classico sauce, olive oil, vinegar, mustard and garlic clove.
Pour dressing over pasta mixture, toss to coat. Cover and chill.
Before serving, toss with olives.

title: party potatoes
directions: Prepare Potato Buds for 8 people as directed on package, except decrease liquid by 1/2 cup.
Mix cream cheese, garlic salt and onion salt; add to potatoes.
Pour into baking dish (buttered).
Pour 1/2 cup butter over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into thin slices. Place in a casserole dish; add potatoes, butter, onion, milk; add salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain.
Add Cheez Whiz, mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Prepare potatoes according to directions on package, omitting butter.
Add cream cheese and butter, stirring until combined. Stir in egg, green onions and parsley.
Spoon potatoes into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yields 4 servings.

title: mattie's chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Boil a roasting hen in 3 quarts of water with celery, onions and bouillon cubes until hen is tender. Discard the vegetables and debone the hen. Cut meat into bite-size pieces. Chill the broth. When cold, remove the chicken fat to use as shortening. Put flour in large bowl with 2 teaspoons salt sifted in. Work in chicken fat and milk (not too moist). Roll out onto a floured surface until very thin. Cut into strips and allow strips to dry. Add broth (Swanson) to chicken broth on hand. Bring to rolling boil with chicken in it. Drop dry strips of dumplings into broth, stirring constantly, until all are added. Reduce heat to simmer. Cover and cook gently until the dumplings are tender. Do not overcook. Serve hot/warm. Serves 12.

title: chocolate halfway bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix shortening, granulated sugar and 1/4 cup brown sugar until very light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, water and vanilla; mix well.
Mix in flour mixture thoroughly.
Pat into baking dish.
Top with chocolate pieces.
Next, beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Spread over chocolate.
Bake for 25 minutes or until done.
Cut into 32 bars while warm.
Cool in dish.
Makes 2 2/3 dozen.

title: french pancake
directions: You will need 2 small bowls or one bowl per person.
Put milk and egg in bowl.
Beat and add flour and mix until smooth.
Set oven at 425°.
Need pie pan (metal or glass) for each person.
Cut butter or oleo; use it to grease pie pan and leave the rest in the pan.
Put in the oven for 5 minutes before you are ready to pour batter in.
Don't let butter or oleo brown.
Quickly pour batter into heated pie pan.
Tilt a bit, but do not stir.
Return to oven; bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Set on hot pad and serve with syrup, jelly or fruit or plain.
The pancake curls up like a bird's nest.
Quick and easy to make.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Make cake as usual but use juice instead of liquid suggested for cake; add water if necessary.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° until done.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese with 1 cup of milk. Add remaining milk with pudding.
Blend this.
Fold in Cool Whip. After cake is baked and cooled, spread on pineapple, then cover with pudding mixture.
Nuts or pineapple may be added.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak
oats
in	boiling water until cool.
Cream sugars with Crisco; add eggs and beat well.
Add oatmeal.
Mix salt, cinnamon, soda
and	flour
together.
Then	add
to
oatmeal mixture. Bake
in
9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Use favorite icing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear cooked chicken into small pieces. Mix soups, Ro-Tel and broth. Pour crushed chips into baking pan. Place chicken on top of chips. Pour liquid over chicken. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels.
Add margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Mix together well.
Press on bottom of pie pan.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then cool.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: Melt morsels, stirring until smooth; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, chocolate and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream or topping.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat
egg well.
Add sugar.
Add
dry
ingredients
and mix. Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan in 400° oven.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Add milk.
This makes thin batter.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon pie filling over batter as evenly as possible.
Bake until batter comes to top and brown.

title: pineapple marshmallow salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water and lemon jello.
Cool.
Mix 7-Up, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Combine with lemon jello and set in refrigerator to set.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine jelly and chili sauce in crock-pot.
Form meat into balls and drop in.
Stir well to coat the meat balls.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together all the dry ingredients.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Top with 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll from the narrow end in the towel.
Cool in refrigerator.
Unroll; spread with filling.

title: mom's rhubarb pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add rhubarb.
Combine sugar, flour and butter.
Add milk; add to rhubarb and stir.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Fold into other mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 40 minutes at 350°, or until golden.

title: cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: no name candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, boil the milk and sugar slowly until the mixture is turning loose from the saucepan.
Next add the vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in molasses. Add 1/4 cup flour, sifted with soda, salt and spices.
Stir thoroughly and add remaining flour, alternating with milk.
Chill dough.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until brown. Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, tomato sauce and paste, Sloppy Joe mix, corn and water. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in salt, sugar, oil and flour.
Add up to 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup of flour at a time. Knead.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Press onto pizza pan (greased). Top with your favorite sauce and toppings and bake.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in baking dish and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: rainy day s'mores
directions: Place butter, evaporated milk, marshmallows, and morsels in the top of a double boiler.
Heat on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until all ingredients are melted. When mixture is smooth, stir in the vanilla extract.
Place the small pieces of broken graham crackers in a large bowl.
Stir in marshmallow mixture until each piece of cracker is well coated.
Put mixture in a 13x9 inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Sprinkle the top with remaining marshmallows.
Allow s'mores to set for about 30 minutes before cutting.
Use a warm knife for easier cutting.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion.
Stir in flour, garlic, celery salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soups.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: grill-side garden salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, zucchini, corn, green onions and avocado in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetable mixture and mix gently.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, occasionally stirring gently.
Stir gently and serve chilled or at room temperature with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings, about 4 cups salad.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender.
Add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Bring to a boil.
Mix flour with water and stir in to thicken.
Extra cheese is good.

title: chicken breast in wine sauce
directions: Mix butter, marjoram, seasoning mix, oregano and parsley together.
Place a dab of mixture in center of each chicken breast.
Add 2 slices of cheese and roll up.
Roll chicken in flour. Dip into egg, water and oil mixture.
Then dip in herb stuffing crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt remaining butter mixture with wine and add to chicken.
Bake 25 minutes more.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Mix molasses with 1 teaspoon soda and add to butter mixture. Beat until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and spices. Add to boiling water, beating until very smooth. Add beaten eggs. Pour into pans to bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and turn on platter. Dust with sifted powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream.

title: yam cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, cream sugar, margarine and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Cut up yams; add to creamed mixture, beating until well mixed.

title: orange chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken for one hour in a combination of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: amish soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add buttermilk and soda. Blend and add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top and bake at 400°
for 7 or 8 minutes.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over bottom and set aside.
Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over nuts in pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together to your liking.
Chill.
May add cooked, chilled green peas to above.
Serve on bed of lettuce with bread sticks, or serve in tomato cups.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Steam onion and carrots separately in microwave or steamer until just tender.
Put chicken stock, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugar, onions and carrots in a pot.
Add cornstarch and bring to a boil until thickened.
Serve hot.

title: minute sauerbraten
directions: Melt butter in skillet; brown meat on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until meat is tender.
Serves 4.

title: baked steak
directions: *Have butcher run meat through cuber.

title: pumpkin spice drop cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend well the flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir coffee and dry ingredients into shortening mixture.
Add pie filling, raisins and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jubilee jumbles(craig todd's favorites)
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls. Bake at 325° until golden brown. Don't overbake.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Blend sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour over butter.
Spoon hot apples over batter.
(Do not stir apples into batter.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add rice.
Pour bouillon and soup over rice.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Arrange over rice. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cover dish with foil.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to directions on package.
Brown sausage with onion and pepper.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients. Place in 2 large or several small glass dishes.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dieters delight salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Add dry jello, fruit cocktail and cottage cheese.
Chill.
Serve.

title: chocolate sour cream fudge
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan with cover, combine sugar, sour cream, chocolate, salt and syrup. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Uncover and cook, stirring frequently, until candy thermometer registers 234° to 240°. Remove from heat. Stir in margarine and vanilla. Cool to 110° without stirring. Beat until creamy and has lost its gloss. Stir in nuts and pour in buttered dish. Chill until hard.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook jello and 1 cup hot water until dissolved.
Add marshmallows and cook until melted.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Prepare both packages of Dream Whip with milk, following directions on box.
Add to mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth; let cool.
Bone chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Strain broth, discarding vegetables.
Return broth to Dutch oven.
Add bouillon granules, carrots, chopped onion and tomatoes; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken, zucchini and peas.
Cover and simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: sicilian chicken with olives
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix vinegar, water, mint and garlic together and pour over chicken.
Liquid should come only 1/3 or 1/2 the depth of the chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Add olives to pan and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: the punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake.
Cool.
Mix vanilla pudding.
Line punch bowl with cherry pie filling.
Place cake on top of filling.
Layer with vanilla pudding. Drain pineapple.
Put a layer of pineapple, topped off with a layer of coconut. Sprinkle pecans on top. Continue this procedure until the punch bowl is full. Top off with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, then cook for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour evenly over popped corn.
Let cool slightly.
Put butter on hands to help keep syrup from sticking and mold into 3 to 4-inch balls.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; beat in oil at a slow drizzle.
Add celery seed.
Goes great on chopped cabbage.

title: sarah's mini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in the mixer.
When soft and fluffy, beat in the eggs and the vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour to make a firm dough.
Cut it with a small cookie cutter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly coloured.
When cool, spread jam between two cookies, then dust it with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix the cooked spaghetti with beaten eggs, milk and grated cheese.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over entire pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
If using a glass pan, lower heat to 325° and cook 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
This recipe can be cut in half.
Bake in a 10-inch round pie pan; makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over the sliced cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 1 hour.
Put into quart jars.
Mix the sugar, white vinegar, celery seed and 1/4 teaspoon powdered alum per jar and boil.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers and seal jar.
Keeps in refrigerator for 1 year.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients like crust.
Pat in long cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: hot buttered pineapple smoothie(drink)
directions: Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar, butter, cloves and cinnamon sticks in a large saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add lemon slices.
Serve hot in mugs.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cinnamon smelly ornaments
directions: You will need a spoon, bowl, rolling pin, cookie cutters, toothpicks, metal cake drying racks and narrow racks.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins, sugar, cold water, lard and salt for 5 minutes after mixing.
Let stand until cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix and bake according to directions on box.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, blend sour cream and egg; set aside.
In a medium bowl or shallow pan, mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip each piece of chicken in sour cream mixture and then roll in bread crumb mixture to coat completely. Place chicken in an oiled shallow baking pan.
Bake until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put milk, water and margarine in boiler.
Melt margarine. Mix cocoa, sugar and flour in bowl, mix well.
Pour mixture into boiler and add 2 egg yolks.
Put in 1 tsp. vanilla, stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: spaghetti squash casserole
directions: Boil
squash
whole in water until fork-tender.
Remove from water
and	cut
lengthwise
when cool enough to handle; scoop out seeds and tough center fibers.
Scoop out flesh with a fork
or spoon; pull flesh apart.
Drain and cool in colander.
Combine onion,
soup
and
sour cream. Stir in shredded carrot;
fold
in drained
squash.
Combine stuffing mix with butter or
margarine. Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 9	x
13-inch
baking dish.
Spoon
vegetable mixture on top. Cover with other half of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Heat pretzels in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 10 minutes.
Melt oleo.
Add dry soup mix; stir well.
Pour over pretzels.
Heat in oven at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: italian herb pie
directions: Shape beef into a patty in a large frying pan.
Brown patty in butter for 5 minutes on each side.
Then place in bowl; break into chunks.
Saute onions in frypan until soft.
Chop tomatoes with juice in pan; add tomato sauce.
Blend in the flour, cheese and seasonings.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mix thickens slightly.
Simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in ground beef.

title: spiced cider
directions: Simmer apple cider with allspice, cinnamon and cloves for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add lemon juice and orange juice. Spices may be tied in cheesecloth to avoid straining.
Serves 10.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 13X9 pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, then cinnamon.
Pour melted butter over rolls and sprinkle with nuts.
Spray plastic wrap with Pam and place over rolls.
Cover with dishtowel and let dough rise overnight.
Bake with cookie sheet under pan at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: mexican roll-ups #2
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Spread on each tortilla. Roll up and chill about 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in medium sized buttered casserole.
Mix melted butter and corn flakes and sprinkle over mixture in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: crunchy apricot cake(upside-up or upside-down)
directions: Spread pie filling on the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: easy to make pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour over butter.
Mix fruit with sugar (if needed) and pour over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious hominy casserole
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in oil for 3 to 5 minutes. Add soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add cheese and seasoning. Fold in 1 can Bush's Best golden hominy.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole which has been well-greased.
Tear one or two slices of bread into small pieces to make soft crumbs.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach dip(low-fat)
directions: Lightly coat a skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Cook and stir onion over medium heat until transparent, about 5 minutes. Add spinach. Cook 1 to 2 minutes until thoroughly heated. Reduce heat. Add cream cheese and stir until melted and smooth. Stir in sour cream, Parmesan cheese and artichokes. Remove from heat. Season with pepper and salt, if desired. Transfer to 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Top with Jack cheese and heat in microwave until cheese melts. Serve warm with reduced-fat crackers or chips of your choice. Yield: 10 servings.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Depending on mix, add raisins, nuts, coconut, etc. if desired.

title: orange spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Spread pecans on ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, orange juice, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Using slotted spoon, remove nuts to foil or waxed paper.
Separate with fork; let dry.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat and stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Finish with pie meringue from egg whites.

title: easy coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove immediately.
Makes about 18 cookies.

title: cashew pea salad
directions: Mix bacon, onions and peas.
Cream mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Pour over pea mixture and mix through.
Chill for several hours (can be made the night before serving).
Add cashews on top just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve broth, debone and cut up into chunks.
Mix
all
ingredients
together, add salt and pepper.
Spread in a large	casserole
dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soften bread crumbs with milk; mix and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Put catsup on top, if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding, sour cream and whipped topping, reserving 1/3 of whipped topping. Alternate layers of wafers, bananas and mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour in greased baking dish (greased with margarine).

title: easy cream puffs
directions: Cut Anginetti's by slicing off tops; set aside.
Drain pineapple, mix Cool Whip and cream cheese for 1 minute.
Add drained pineapple and mix for 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling on bottom layer of cookie and replace top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, horseradish, poppy seed and onions.
Spread on sandwich.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy sweet-n-sour meat balls
directions: Mix meat, salt and pepper, 1/2 cup rice and egg.
Make small meat balls (set aside).
In a large pot, combine chili sauce, grape jelly and water.
Mix well.
Add meat balls.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour into a greased casserole or 13 x 7-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
This is very good for a large family or could be divided and 1 casserole be frozen for later.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine the juice, rind, shortening and enough water to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Add juice mixture to dry ingredients.
Add egg.
Mix just enough to blend.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Better when a day or two old.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes on a well-greased and floured cookie sheet with lip.

title: kathy's mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and taco seasoning.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread refried beans over meat.
Layer on cheese, chilies and taco sauce.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Remove; cool slightly.
Spread sour cream on top.
Garnish with green onions, olives and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bruised red cabbage and apples
directions: Melt bacon fat or butter.
Add sugar; stir until brown.
Add chopped onion; cook until golden.
Add red cabbage, apples, vinegar, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until tender, adding water (or red wine) as necessary to keep from sticking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill 9-inch pie shell while making filling.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into chilled unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Cool 15 to 30 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chili (mild)
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain fat.
Rinse kidney beans. Combine chopped onions, chopped tomatoes and chopped green pepper. Put all together in a large kettle.
Cook for 4 hours.
Stir about every 15 minutes or so, on low heat.

title: mountain mama mud slide pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly and press into an oblong baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: glazed apples
directions: Use hard, tart apples, not Delicious.
Peel and core them (any desired amount).
Put water and sugar in saucepan and boil for about 10 minutes, half covered with liquid.
Place apples in boiling water syrup and cook about 5 minutes.
Cover apples with the sauce gently over and over with this sauce.
Repeat until they are tender to the touch of a fork.
Add about 3 red cinnamon candies to the sauce.
Add lemon juice.
Add vanilla and salt. Place 1/4 teaspoon butter in the cavity of each apple when you turn out fire.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon jelly in each cavity of the apples.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables; cook until vegetables are tender.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Stir together. Keep warm.
Serve with Doritos.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter a cookie sheet.
Mix syrup, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add nuts and bring to a boil and cook to the hard crack stage (300`° to 310°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda quickly.
Pour immediately onto buttered cookie sheet and spread.
Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: chicken stock
directions: Place chicken in pot and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Remove chicken from pot.
Strain through a sieve on cheesecloth.
Allow stock to cool for several hours or until fat solidifies.
Skim off fat.
Bring broth to a boil.
Pour into hot jars leaving 1-inch headspace.
Process pints 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: salsa mac
directions: Brown meat in large skillet. Drain. Stir in salsa and water. Bring to boil. Stir in macaroni. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Add Velveeta. Stir until melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: molded beet salad
directions: Bring to a boil beet juice, sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and onion salt.
Boil 2 minutes; add lemon Jell-O.
Refrigerate until jells a little, then add celery and shoestring beets.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with sour cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together; drain and add chicken soup, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and olives.
Stir all together.
Line 9 x 12-inch dish with tortilla chips and layer meat mixture and cheese; leaving crushed tortilla chips on top. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for about 1 hour and serve.

title: stollen german christmas bread
directions: Combine 5 cups of flour, cinnamon, mace and cardamom.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Stir in the oil, vanilla, eggs and walnuts.
The batter will be very thick.
Add apples and mix well.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use a pan with a removable bottom or the cake will be hard to remove.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.
No frosting is necessary.

title: d's wedding punch
directions: Mix well for an excellent flavor.

title: luscious lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: tuna ball
directions: Combine ingredients, shape into ball, roll in parsley then in nuts.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Mix together and bake, covered, for 35 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mini carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/3 of potatoes and carrots into an 8-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese and nutmeg, pepper to taste.
Alternate for 2 more layers in the same fashion.
Bring broth to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake casserole for 45 minutes or until top is brown.
If vegetables begin to dry out, add more broth.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ritz peanut butter and cracker cookies
directions: Melt white chocolate in double boiler.
Make peanut butter and crackers.
Drop peanut butter and crackers into the white chocolate until well coated.
Place onto wax paper.
Let cool. Makes great cookies.

title: no fail chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients except eggs in a bowl and beat until creamy.
Add eggs and finish beating.
Bake in 350° oven for 38 minutes.

title: easy sandwich spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise (you can use low-cal cheese and diet mayonnaise).
Stir in pecans, salad olives, liquid and dash of pepper.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
This makes a great sandwich, especially when served on lettuce leaves with your bread or bun.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken; remove from broth.
Debone and cut.
Add soup; bring to low boil, blending soup with broth well.
Add cut up chicken to broth.
Cut flour tortillas in half, then each half into several small pieces.
Drop tortilla pieces into boiling broth.
Cook on medium heat, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Reduce to simmer and cover.

title: sausage hash brown pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together hash browns, butter and bouillon.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown sausage and onion; drain fat.
Combine eggs and cheese with meat mixture; pour onto hash brown crust.
Sprinkle top with reserved shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Place the first six ingredients in a slow cooker and stir gently.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Yield: 16 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put lettuce in bottom of salad bowl. Add cauliflower and onion; add just enough mayo to cover top. Sprinkle dry salad dressing mix on top. Add about 12 shakes of vinegar bottle to top of mayo; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Add crumbled bacon; cover and refrigerate overnight or until serving time, then mix and serve.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Saute onion in oil.
Put together and add the following:
kidney beans, tomato soup, V-8 juice, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic new potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes, covered, in boiling salted water for 15 minutes
or
until tender; drain.
Saute garlic in butter in a small skillet
until
tender.
Add parsley and pepper to skillet. Pour
mixture
over
potatoes,
tossing gently to cover. Yields 6 servings.

title: summertime tea
directions: Steep tea and boiling water for 5 minutes in a gallon container, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, lemonade and limeade.
Stir in steeped tea.
Add 10 cups water.
Keeps good in refrigerator.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Put sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes and set aside, then blend in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Let cool.
Makes approximately 20 cookies.

title: "never fail" lemon meringue pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water and butter in a 2-quart microwave bowl. Microwave on High setting about 3 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.
Mix cornstarch with cold water; stir into sugar and butter mixture. Cook in microwave for 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Remove from microwave and stir in lemon juice and lemon zest.
Beat egg yolks with milk and stir slowly into cornstarch mixture.
Return to microwave for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Cool and pour into pie shell.

title: decorator icing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with broth.
Spread soup over chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix well, flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 2 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine everything.
Pour into pan. Cover with foil. Cook in preheated oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple-pecan boat
directions: Combine ingredients and place in fresh pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix beef, cracker crumbs, milk, eggs, salt and pepper together and form into balls.
Brown on all sides in skillet or place on cookie sheet and bake approximately 20 minutes.
Boil ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, water, brown sugar and onion. Bring mixture to full boil; simmer until onion is tender.
Pour over meat balls.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Stir until dissolved.
In separate bowl, combine cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
Stir in vinegar mixture.
Let set for a few minutes.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown,	stir
and drain beef.
Stir
in
tomato
paste, onion and seasoning.
Mixture will be thick.
Cook
over	low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Place biscuits in greased muffin pans, pressing to cover bottoms and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined	cups
and sprinkle with
cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes
or
until
golden brown.
Makes 12 pizza cups.

title: pasta salad - lu's
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 7 ingredients.
Using whisk or fork, gradually beat in oil until well combined.

title: busy day halibut
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Dry well.
Cut into 6 portions.
Combine soup mix and sour cream.
In separate bowl mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and paprika.
Dip fish in sour cream mixture.
Roll in bread crumb mixture.
