Place in single layer on aluminum foil in well-greased pan or broiler pan.
Pour butter or oil over fish. Bake at 475° to 500° for 10 to 12 minutes until fish flakes easily. Yields 6 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Measure all ingredients into a bowl, blending 1/2 minute on low speed.
Continue beating until well blended.
Pour into pan. Bake 50
minutes.
Serve
warm
with whipped
cream
or applesauce.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Measure the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt right into the cake pan and mix it.
Make 3 holes in the dry cake mix. Measure the vegetable oil into one hole, the vinegar into the second hole and the vanilla into the third hole.
Pour the water over all of the mixture and mix it in.
It looks just like you're mixing a mud pie, but you aren't.
Be sure that you stir all the flour in so that there aren't any lumps.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Wash strawberries; set aside to drain while preparing cake. Cut angel food cake; tear out some cake in the middle to add ingredients.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip followed by a layer of glaze and strawberries, then replace cake.
Add Cool Whip, glaze and strawberries.
Take top part of cake; place on cake and cover with same steps as before until all ingredients are gone.
Can spoon some juice over finished cake to add moisture if desired.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Rinse, dry and slice fresh mushrooms (5 cups) or drain canned mushrooms, reserving liquid.
In large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons oil.
Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken; brown.
Remove and set aside.
To skillet, add celery, onion, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water or reserved mushroom liquid (makes 2 cups).
Stir in skillet along with soy sauce, salt, ginger and red pepper.
Return chicken, uncovered, until tender, 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, heat and serve with steamed rice.

title: barbecued spoonburgers
directions: Brown ground beef in hot shortening in skillet.
Discard excess fat.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker, stir thoroughly. Cover and cook on high 3 to 4 hours.
Spoon into split, warmed hamburger buns or serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: german spinach
directions: Fry diced bacon and chopped onion together in a large frying pan with 1 tablespoon oil. Cook until bacon is just brown and onion is tender. While bacon and onion are frying, wash and stem fresh spinach.

Cook spinach until just done. Do not add any water. If you use frozen spinach, cook per directions on box. Drain well. When bacon and onion are done, add 1 tablespoon flour and stir until it forms a roux (white gravy). Add balance of flour with a little water until you have a nice roux.
Add a little more water if roux is too thick. Add cooked spinach to mixture and toss well, coating all the spinach. Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Place chicken breast in greased casserole dish.
Place cheese on top.
Mix soup and sherry. Pour on top.
Place dressing on top.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant caesar salad
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients in blender until smooth to make dressing.
Toss dressing with romaine lettuce, croutons and Romano cheese.

title: ham and cheese bites
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and onions.
Spread mixture evenly on ham slices using about 2 tablespoons per slice.
Roll slices.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Cut each slice into 6 pieces.

title: stuffed chayote
directions: Peel the chayotes; cut them in half to take the pits off. Slice them thick and put them in water to boil.
Save water when finished.
Let cool.
Take one slice; top with slice of Mozzarella cheese and put another slice of chayote on top.
Squeeze together to drain liquid with hands.
Dip them in egg mixture and fry patties in a skillet with half an inch of oil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup liquid.
Boil liquid; dissolve Jell-O.
Add 1 cup water.
Chill until thick but not set.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken wings - buffalo style
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° (high) for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.
Combine hot sauce and butter.
Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip or for equally crispy wings, bake on a rack in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour; turn halfway through cooking time.

title: salmon salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mold into small dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika for relish.
Great for holidays.

title: green beans
directions: Brown bacon; pour off drippings and drain on paper towel. Add to bacon drippings the salt, vinegar and sugar.
Cook until syrup. Add green beans and onion. Cook until onion is tender. Add crumbled bacon to top.

title: christmas slaw
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and let cool.
Chop cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Add can of pimento.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Let set 12 to 24 hours.
Stir several times.
It keeps a couple of weeks.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water with salts and curry powder added.
Remove when tender and save stock.
Dice chicken.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add to stock.
Add bouillon and bring to boil.
Add corn and rice and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until thick.
Stir frequently.
Add chicken and simmer another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with cornbread and tossed salad.
(This will keep for several hours in a crock-pot on warm.)

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Put mixture into pie crust and top with 21 oz. can cherry pie filling. May also use blueberries.

title: the best pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.

Add lemon and vanilla extracts. Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then decrease temperature to 325° and continue baking for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tester is clean. Makes 16 servings.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies or bars
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients, then add liquid ingredients. Cook at 350° on cookie sheet or put in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Cut after cooled.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, vanilla, flour, chips and pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and form into 1 inch balls.
Back 15 minutes on ungreased cooking sheet until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: molasses cake bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix in molasses and water.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While warm, frost with confectioners icing.

title: meat country pie
directions: Mix meat mixture with ingredients and pat into bottom of pie plate and up sides, using only 1/2 of tomato sauce.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef; add cabbage and enough water to cover.
Add onion, beef bouillon, garlic powder or salt, celery, kidney beans and tomatoes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water and remaining ingredients; beat well.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps up to 10 days.
Beat batter when removing from refrigerator.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Fold the dry mixture in the pumpkin mixture.
Spread in a greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Put the cake on a powdered sugar cloth and roll it.
Let it cool.
Unroll and fill with the filling:

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage, pepper and onion.
Add sauerkraut.
Let cook about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Delicious served on top of mashed potatoes.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Bake or boil potatoes until just tender.
Peel and shred into large bowl.
Toss with cheese, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 2 quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Pour cream over. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Delicious!

title: champagne punch
directions: Chill all the ingredients and mix well.
Float the lemon and lime in the punch.

title: cube steak with cream sauce
directions: Dust both sides of cube steaks with flour.
Place them in a skillet of hot oil.
Salt and pepper steaks.
Brown on each side. Pour off grease; add water and mushrooms.
Lower heat, cover and simmer until water has cooked down.
Then add soup and milk. Cover and cook on low for another 30 to 45 minutes until done. Good with buttered noodles.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add broccoli.
Cook until tender. Blend in Cheez Whiz and soup.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Place into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine sifted flour and soda and add to cream mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° until cake looks done, about 25 minutes. Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg and milk; beat until smooth.
Peel and core apples.
Slice into 4 equal slices. Dip each slice in batter and fry in deep fat at 350°.
Serve hot, sprinkled with 10x sugar.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients as you would for a cake.
Beat eggs thoroughly and slowly pour in mixture.
Pour in pineapple (including juice).
Pour in unbaked shell and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in syrup.
Add eggs slowly, stirring until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes longer until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Mix flour, breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese. Flatten chicken breasts.
Dip in milk and egg mixture, then in flour, breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese mixture.
Fry in oil until brown.
Pour spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish; layer chicken breasts, then sauce.
Top with sliced Provolone cheese and sliced pepperoni.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: amish cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar in bottom of Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 325°. Eat plain or with icing.

title: spanish potato omelet
directions: Fry bacon in 10 inch skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon & drain, reserving 4 Tbsp. bacon fat in skillet. Cook and stir potato & onion until potato is golden brown & tender, about 10 minutes.

title: yummy potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 300° (or 1 hour at 375°).
Remove foil for last 20 minutes of baking.

title: apple-bread pudding
directions: Spread bread with margarine and toast in oven.
Cut toasted bread into cubes and place in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan greased with margarine.
Add apples.
Mix egg substitute, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk and water together in a separate bowl.
Pour mixture over apples and let set 10 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat together until smooth and spread on cake.
Re-roll cake and chill.
(Oblong plastic container helps keep shape.)
Can also use two 8 x 8-inch pans and put filling in middle.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Mix and let set a short time before serving.
Serves 8.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in microwave.
Add peanut butter. Blend/mix into cereal until evenly coated.
Place mixture into large bowl or plastic bag.
Add powdered sugar and shake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pluck and clean birds.
Cut up in pieces.
Put in kettle with water and salt.
Cut up 1 onion into small pieces.
Let all boil until birds are done and thicken with flour.
Let boil for a few minutes longer, then add duck meat.

title: lemon mushroom chicken
directions: Brown the chicken breasts in the clarified butter. Add the mushrooms and cook over low heat until mushrooms are tender and chicken is firm. Add the lemon juice and simmer for 30 seconds or more. Season with salt and pepper.
Put over cooked rice.

title: eggs on toast(kids cake)
directions: Slice a piece of toast. Top with a peach half, rounded "sunnyside" side up.
Squirt whipped topping around "egg."

title: miss betty's spinach casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The last 20 minutes, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cracker cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Beat egg whites and vanilla until small peaks.
Gradually add sugar to egg whites while beating until stiff peaks, but not dry.
Carefully fold dry mixture into egg whites.
Line cake pans with aluminum foil, shiny side up.
Grease foil and divide the batter evenly into pans. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Lift foil from pan and peel foil away from layers.

title: hot pepper jam
directions: Cut peppers into pieces after washing well and removing any spots.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Quarter onions and puree.
In a 3-quart casserole or other large transparent microwave-safe bowl, mix peppers, onions, sugar and vinegar. Microwave on High, uncovered, about 12 minutes, bringing mixture to a brisk boil.
Boil on High for 5 minutes.
Add pectin and a few drops of food coloring.
Microwave on High about 5 minutes until mixture returns to a boil.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Skim foam with large spoon.
Pour immediately into sterilized jars to within 1/8-inch of top.
Wipe jars.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind together cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle salt over mixture and let stand for 1 hour; drain juice off.
In a big pan, put sugar, white vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and alum.
Bring to boil.
Add cucumber mixture and bring back to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal in hot water bath 10 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar, salt and 1 cup flour.
Add remaining flour and yeast mixture.
Let rise to double in size.
Pinch dough into small balls and place 3 balls in each greased muffin hole.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: preston's potato soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add onions, celery, carrots and margarine; cook about 8 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add can of evaporated milk and extra water (approximately a pint to a quart).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Instant potatoes may be added for extra thickness.
Makes about 1 gallon. May be refrigerated for 5 to 6 days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together and bake
in a 9-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture. Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix the six cans together in a crock-pot and set on high until thoroughly warm, then set on low.
Serve over Fritos.
It's delicious!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add mayonnaise to macaroni.
Add flaked tuna, sweet relish, parsley flakes, carrot, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Put chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pepper the pieces.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese boneless chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in egg-milk mixture, then batter in fish fry.
In wok heat oil and fry chicken pieces.
Remove chicken and almost all of the oil.
Reheat wok and add onion, celery, bell pepper, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Stir-fry for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth to mixture.
Let simmer for 5 minutes. Use cornstarch to thicken.
After mixture is at desired consistency, pour over chicken pieces.
Serve with Chinese fried rice.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Potatoes can be added 2 hours before stew is done.

title: the wonderful yellow sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake in floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; pat evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot shredded meat sandwiches
directions: Simmer all ingredient for 5 to 7 hours.
When meat is tender enough, shred it with a fork.
Cook until liquid is thick.
Serve over crusty sourdough rolls.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries in small saucepan.
Add water and bring to boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Strain juice from cooked berries.
Add water if needed to make 1 cup; reserve.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in same saucepan and reserved juice stirring until smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook about 3 minutes until thick and clear.
Add food coloring.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour over berries which have been arranged in pastry shell.
Serve with whipped cream.
Be sure to coat each berries with glaze.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat.
Add 1/2
cup water and simmer (don't boil) until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple and combine juice with brown sugar,
cornstarch,
vinegar,
soya sauce and salt. Add to pork and cook
until
thick,
to
minutes.	Add pineapple and onion.	Serve
with
rice
or chow mein noodles. Serves 4 or 6 (use 3 or 4 steaks for 6).

title: chicken in marinade(japanese style)
directions: Marinate 6 to 8 chicken parts (recommend skinless) at least two hours, basting or turning pieces often.
Bake chicken in the marinade for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: bogracs gulyas(kettle goulash)
directions: Heat the lard in a 4 or 5-quart heavy saucepan until a light haze forms over it, then reduce the heat to medium.
Add the onions and garlic; cook them 8 to 10 minutes, or until the onions are lightly colored.
Off the heat, stir in the paprika.
Stir until the onions are well coated.
Add the beef cubes, caraway seed and stock or water to the pan; season with the salt and pepper.
Bring the liquid to a boil and partially cover the pan. Simmer for 1 hour, or until the beef is almost tender.

title: danish
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, 1 stick butter and cold water.
Pat in 6 x 12-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
Boil 1 cup water, 1 stick butter and 1 cup flour.
Stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Add almond extract.
Spread over the rectangle of dough.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Add sugar, flour, margarine and eggs; mix with a fork.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This will make 2 thin pies or one large pie.

title: acorn squash
directions: Wash squash and split lengthwise; scrape out seeds. Place cut side down on baking sheet lined with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until squash is tender.
Turn squash over.
Add 1/2 slice bacon, butter, salt and pepper to each. Return to oven and bake for 30 minutes longer or until bacon is cooked. Yields 6 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter a loaf pan and set aside. Combine the flour, sugar and beer. Mix well. The mixture should be sticky. Pour into the loaf pan and bake for 55 minutes. At the last 3 minutes of baking, remove from oven; brush the top of the loaf with butter and return to oven. Cool. Slice and enjoy.

title: easy punch(makes one punch bowl)
directions: Pour juice and Kist cola into punch bowl.
Fill bowl up with ice.
Garnish with orange slices if desired.

title: ribbon cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and powder.
Blend in butter with hands until like corn meal.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Use spoon, work into a stiff dough.
Divide into 2 balls, 1 twice the size of the other. On heavily floured board (1/2 cup flour), roll out the larger ball to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place on cookie sheet (11 x 15 1/2-inches). Smooth to edges; patch corners.
Spread jelly over top.
Roll out remaining dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 1/2-inch strips. Place diagonally across jelly 1/2-inch apart.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Start baking in a 375° oven.
Edges will be done first.
When edges brown (about 20 minutes), take pan from oven and cut 3-inch strip all around.
Return pan to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and cut into 1-inch and 2-inch rectangles.
Keeps 6 weeks.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust. Place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed, salt and sugar to a boil.
Mix vegetables well. Pour liquid solution over vegetables. Store in refrigerator.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix egg yolks and water; beat until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Fold in flour mixture.
Bake 20 minutes on waxed paper on greased cookie sheet at 350°.
Remove wax paper and spread jelly immediately; roll.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: swedish meat balls (or meat loaf)
directions: Pour hot milk over crumbs, add eggs and seasonings, then mix in meat. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes depending on size. Also this recipe I use for meat loaf and that is also in 350° oven and takes about an hour, draining off fat every once in a while. (I put ketchup on the top.)

title: real chili
directions: Dice beef into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes and brown in oil in a large cast-iron kettle.
Cover with water and boil 1 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Quarter tomatoes, dice garlic, chop onion, slice jalapeno peppers and add 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with tortilla, rice, salsa and cheese.
To increase "macho" increase peppers.
This recipe is "semi-macho".
(Anyone who knows beans about chili knows there ain't no beans in chili!)

title: suzy's christmas egg bake
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Top bread with cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix together eggs, scalded milk, sausage, onion/pepper mixture, jalepeno peppers and dry mustard. Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and remaining milk and pour mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown and set.

title: pork noodles
directions: Brown pork chops, then steam until tender.
Remove bones and cube.
Chop onion and eggs, then place in separate containers. Cook egg noodles.
Drain and add bouillon, heating thoroughly. Spoon noodles and bouillon into serving dishes.
Top with the cubed pork, chopped eggs and onion.

title: algonquin deer meat stew
directions: Place meat in slow cooker or in pan on stove at medium heat until tender.
Add onion and carrots.
Add potatoes last.
Make gravy with meat juice and flour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate cooked vermicelli in mixture of Italian dressing, lemon juice, Accent, garlic salt and black pepper overnight.
Next day, add celery, green pepper, black olives and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add the meat to salad when ready to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.

title: chicken-cheese bake
directions: In the morning or the day before, put whole chicken breasts, wrapped in foil, in the oven and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 cups, cubed.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Firmly press mixture in bottom of dish and set aside.

title: shell macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells. Cook just until done, not mushy.
Drain and rinse in cold water until no heat is left in them.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In small saucepan, boil onions and peppers in water.
Simmer until veggies are crisp, but tender.
Drain well.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish (all sides and bottom).
Mix together remaining ingredients and veggies.
Transfer to baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes (you can add cheese on top if you like).

title: chili meat loaf with green pepper
directions: Mix in order given, except for green peppers.
Put into greased baking pan.
Press the large pieces of bell pepper into the mixture sideways so they will fit.
Cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until peppers are done.

title: asparagus casserole with cheese sauce
directions: Melt your butter over very low heat; add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk, stirring continuously.
Next, add the dissolved chicken bouillon, still stirring.
Add Cheddar cheese, stirring continuously.
By the time the cheese has melted you should have a rich creamy sauce; now add salt and pepper.
Arrange quartered toast in baking dish and place drained asparagus on top of toast.
Pour cheese sauce over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until the cheese sauce is bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: gooby cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and press in greased and floured pan (10 x 12-inch).
Then add crushed pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven until light brown.

title: lemony brussels sprouts
directions: Cut an x in the core of each Brussels sprout. Place in a saucepan; add 1-inch of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain.
In a large skillet, saute the sprouts, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper
in butter for 2 to 3 minutes or until flavors are blended.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute onion, celery, green peppers and mushrooms in 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Mix soy sauce, bouillon, ginger and water.
Add all ingredients in saute pan.
Heat thoroughly and serve on rice or chow mein noodles.

title: caponata
directions: Cook (saute) first 6 ingredients about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly until vegetables are completely cooked.
Use a cover on pan.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin bisque
directions: Saute onion, celery and parsley in butter until limp. Add pumpkin and cook until tender.
In saucepan, combine chicken broth, milk, cream and spices. Blend thoroughly.
Add vegetables and heat to simmer for 5 minutes until thick.

title: quick veggie mix
directions: Chop the first three ingredients together and saute in 1 teaspoon cooking oil.
Add mushrooms and pimentos.
Cook together until onion and bell pepper become tender.
Add corn and green beans.
Stir until warm.
Decorate with almonds.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour in pie shell.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken strips in large Ziploc bag.
Pour in Italian dressing, crushed red pepper and garlic powder and zip shut. Marinate for at least one hour.
Can be refrigerated and left overnight.
Heat butter in frying pan and add chicken.
Cook until chicken is done.
Serve with linguine, tossed salad and Italian bread.

title: earth cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pan with nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on the box.
Spread over unbaked cake a mixture of cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can serve with Cool Whip.

title: mrs. farlin's date torte(very good)
directions: Combine dates, soda and water.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Bake in sheet pan and cut into 2-inch pieces when cool.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and chicken; brown 10 minutes.
Add water, cover and simmer until tender. Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings and mix well.
Add cooked noodles.
Arrange chicken on top.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mint tea
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add 8 tea bags.
Drop fresh mint in. Boil for 30 minutes.
Add other ingredients and then enough water to make a gallon of tea.

title: ribs
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine on medium heat, stirring all the time.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until tender. Remove from heat.
Cook ribs on outside grill 1/2 hour.
Put in roaster.
Add sauce and salt to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cajun red potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except potatoes. Toss with warm potatoes.
Cover and chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: stephanie mclaughlin's banana pudding
directions: Make pudding with milk.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Top with pudding and chill.

title: farmer's fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Add apples, milk, sugar and beaten egg.
Stir just until moistened.
Drop batter by tablespoons, four or five at a time, into hot cooking oil (375°).
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll hot fritters in mixture of sugar and ground cinnamon.

title: sour cream coffee cake(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter with 3/4 of the sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Sift the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda and add, blending well. Mix in the sour cream and the vanilla.

title: zesty italian casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot.
Combine cheese and sour cream in bowl. Pour hot meat mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon sour cream and cheese mixture on top of meat and spread evenly.
Place flat crescent rolls on top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top of crescents.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin flavors separately, using 1 cup boiling water for each.
Stir marshmallows into lemon gelatin and set aside.
Add 3/4 cup cold water to lime gelatin; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set but not firm.
Add 3/4 cup cold water to raspberry gelatin.
Set aside at room temperature.
Add cream cheese to lemon mixture; beat until well blended.
Chill until thickened, then blend in mayonnaise, whipped cream and crushed pineapple.
Chill until very thick; spoon gently over lime gelatin.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: beef and sausage dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Cut cheese into small blocks and put into crock-pot.
Put in cream of mushroom soup and melt with cheese.
When cheese and soup are melted, put in beef and sausage.
Serve in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: wasp cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding together.
Heat on medium heat until just boiling.
Add cake mix and blend until smooth.
Add pecan chips. Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar.
Add butter and mix well. Pat dough into 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cathy's hot dip
directions: Use large 8 x 14-inch (approximately) glass pan.
Spoon and spread cream cheese on bottom.
Spoon picante sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Heat in microwave for 4 minutes.
Serve with Fritos.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and
flour.
Beat eggs thoroughly; add to the sugar and flour mixture.
Add melted margarine and buttermilk; mix well.
Add
extracts
and
pour into chilled 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake
at
for	10
minutes,
then reduce temperature to 350°
and continue baking for 35 minutes without opening door.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add sugar, vanilla and oil to beaten eggs, blending well. Stir in zucchini gradually.
Add dry ingredients; fold in nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Place onto cooling racks.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Chill slightly.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes until browned on the bottom.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, margarine and vanilla, then add oats.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 325 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: miss kate's frozen tea(makes one gallon)
directions: Squeeze lemons and oranges.
Chill juices and reserve lemon hulls.
Boil 2 quarts of water.
Remove from heat and add tea bags, mint leaves and reserved lemon hulls.
Steep 30 minutes.
Strain. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours. When mixture is thoroughly cooled, add lemon, orange and cherry juices, plus 1 1/2-quarts more cold water.
Stir well and freeze in 1 gallon ice cream freezer to slushy consistency.
When serving, garnish with mint and cherry.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
It takes 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water for hot cocoa.

title: leeann's mac & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Mix cheese soup, the cheese that comes with macaroni and 1/2 can evaporated milk.
Stir well.
Add macaroni; pour in a casserole dish; sprinkle shredded cheese over top (not to much).
Bake at 350 until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: *Tip:
Use Egg Beaters and 2% milk to reduce fat.

title: easy fudge
directions: In medium pot on low heat, melt chips and milk; when melted, remove from heat.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill and cut into pieces.
Peanut butter sets up faster than chocolate.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in large dishpan.
Place sugar, cream of tartar and water in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Place cover on pan and boil 5 minutes on medium, stirring occasionally. Uncover pan and continue cooking without stirring for about 10 minutes or when color starts to change.
Do not cook until it turns dark.
Remove from heat, add margarine and soda and mix thoroughly. Pour quickly over popcorn.
Stir to coat.
Let cool slightly and separate.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually.
Cream
until fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture. Divide dough.
Roll chilled dough on floured pastry cloth to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on unbuttered cookie sheet about 6 minutes at 400°. Cool on rack.

title: 12 layer chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Let margarine and butter soften.
Add sugar.
Beat until well mixed. Put 2 mixing spoons of batter in well-greased pan.
Place in preheated oven and bake until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to first mixture.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Mix soda and vinegar over bowl; add to batter and blend.
Bake at 350° in oblong pan 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and cook.
Top with caramel icing.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Then lower temperature to 325° and bake 10 more minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan and cool before frosting.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except jelly and chili sauce. Shape in 1-inch meatballs and brown lightly in skillet.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in Dutch oven. Stir well. Add meatballs.
Stir until cooked.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 to 5 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt, cornstarch and boiling water; cook until thick. Remove from heat and cool. Add jello and strawberries. When it begins to jell, pour into baked pie shell. Top with cool whip.

title: lo-cal ranch dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor or blender.
If desired, may add 4 tablespoons onion or dehydrated onion and/or 4 tablespoons vegetable flakes.
Two tablespoons are considered free on most food plans.

title: cinnamon nut coffee cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Don't mix. Just layer the first 3 ingredients in a bowl; cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator. The next day, mix the Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar; let set 20 minutes so that the sugar will dissolve.
Add the dressing to the vegetable mixture, then add the sunflower kernels, raisins, cheese and bacon bits.

title: "mama's" chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, egg yolks, flour and milk.
Stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Heat over low heat until mixture thickens (stir constantly).
Remove from heat; let cool and add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: honey twist yeast coffee cake
directions: Pour hot milk over butter and sugar.
Crumble yeast into lukewarm water.
Cool milk to lukewarm, add yeast and well-beaten eggs.
Beat in flour to make soft dough, then turn on floured board and knead until smooth.
Form into ball and place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Combine the sugar, butter and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook at 300° (to hard crack stage), stirring constantly without burning.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay 2 chocolate bars on top and spread them evenly as they melt. While still warm, sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Cool thoroughly and break into pieces.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Note:
If you have any mixture leftover, refrigerate for hamburgers or meat loaf.

title: budget beef burgundy
directions: Do not brown beef, use raw beef; stir all together.
Put in 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; stir.
Cover tightly; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.
Mushrooms and/or water chestnuts may be added.
Do not add tomatoes or potatoes.
Can be served over noodles or rice.

title: dumplings
directions: Add enough milk to make stiff like pie crust.
Roll into ball on floured board and roll out like pie crust.
Cut into strips and let dry.
Drop into soup.

title: surprise bites
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add flour, Tabasco sauce, salt and paprika.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 4 dozen.
(Olives may be omitted.)

title: applesauce topping
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Cut in 1/4 cup of cold butter until crumbly.
Add nuts and oats.
Sprinkle over applesauce.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake until brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crisp chocolate marshmallow treat
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add Andes and hot water.
Stir until melted.
Add another spoon of hot water if needed.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in rice crispy cereal, sunflower seeds and raisins.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly greased.
Refrigerate to cool.
Cut into bars.

title: bean casserole for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large roaster.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; blend well and set aside.
Beat egg whites until peaks form; set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, oil and egg yolks; beat well. Mix in sweet potato and nuts.
Blend in dry ingredients and hot water, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan; bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until done.

title: oreo cookie ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble 1/2 of the cookies into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour some of the chocolate syrup over the cookies.
Mix and pat back down into pan.
Layer 1/2 of the ice cream.
Slice it off.
Dribble chocolate syrup over this and then add cookie crumbs.
Syrup over this, then layer with ice cream.
Dribble chocolate syrup over this again if you want more chocolate taste.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Can put cookies around to decorate or sprinkle cookie crumbs on top.
Can add cherries.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Melt bacon drippings; add onion and cook until golden brown. Add 1/2 cup hot water to flour and salt and mix.
Add shredded cabbage and 1 large apple (cut in small pieces, optional).
Simmer until tender.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine sauces with seasonings. Put a very small amount of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook noodles.
Make layer of noodles, layer of sauce, layer of meat and half of each of the cheeses.
Use rest of ingredients to make second series of noodles, meat, sauce and cheeses.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; add blueberries, lemon juice, lemon peel, cinnamon and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 4 to 6 minutes or until thickened.
Place in 4-cup baking dish.
Spoon Cobbler Topping over fruit mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cole slaw for 100
directions: Shred all ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, oil and vinegar.
Heat this and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, stir into milk; use a double boiler. Cook over heat stirring until mixture coats a spoon (begins to thicken).
Cool immediately adding vanilla.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Place in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain off liquid.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Sift together into a large bowl.
Add oil, apples and vanilla.
Beat by hand or on medium speed the eggs until light yellow in color.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Fold the egg mixture into the apple mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cold.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Set aside.
Melt caramels, evaporated milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Now add caramel mixture, chocolate chips on top of that, then pecans and top with rest of batter. Bake 20 minutes more.

title: cheese-pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and chill.
When nearly jelled (1 to 1 1/2 hours), combine cream cheese and whipped cream.
Mix all ingredients together and chill to jell.

title: whole wheat banana bread(from new york times national foods cookbook)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift wheat and white flour, baking soda and salt.
Combine bananas and buttermilk or yogurt enough to mix.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream
together
butter, peanut butter, white and brown sugars and
vanilla.
Then
add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased pan and bake in moderate oven.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix together soy sauce, sugar, garlic and mustard.
Pour over wings and marinate overnight.
Bake in sauce 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini and shrimp fritters
directions: Heat the oil in a

skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onions; season with salt and cayenne and cook, stirring, until the onions are soft, about 3 minutes. Add the shrimp and cook, stirring, until they turn pink, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and set aside.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate over night for best flavor, but can be made and served right away.
This is a popular hors d'oeuvre served with crackers!

title: tropical fruit n' nut bars
directions: Drain pineapple well, pressing out juice with back of spoon (1 1/4 cups).
In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over reserved juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in honey, pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Turn into 8 or 9-inch baking pan. Chill until firm.

title: zucchini-buttermilk soup
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except buttermilk.
Cover and vent.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, stirring once until vegetables are softened.
Pour into blender on low speed.
Pour back into casserole with buttermilk.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds until hot.
Serves 2.
Contains 80 calories, 1 gm fat and 549 mg sodium.

title: tetraginni (pasta)
directions: Combine cooked vermicelli with remaining ingredients and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine yeast and 1 cup flour in large bowl.
Heat water, sugar and salt until just warm.
Add to dry mixture.
Beat on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl, turn and grease surface.
Cover, let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with corn meal.
Knead bread.
Put in casserole dish in warmed oven.
Let rise until doubled, 40 to 60 minutes.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate and butterscotch candy
directions: Melt morsels and chips in bowl in microwave.
Take out and add pecans.
Drop onto 2 cookie sheets in small bits and set in refrigerator until hard.

title: blair "goulash"
directions: Brown beef in large, deep pan.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Drain excess fat.
Add garlic salt, chili powder, tomatoes and juice and water. Bring to a boil. Add macaroni.
Cook at medium temperature until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Spoon into puff pastry shells to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, put into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: spicy corn chowder(servings: 6)
directions: Heat olive oil in a large heavy-bottom soup pot. Saute corn, onions, carrots, celery and bell pepper over medium heat for 20 minutes or until soft. Add serrano pepper and spices. Stir to mix well and cook 5 minutes longer. Add stock and cream; mix well. Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: kitty's gobble burgers
directions: Drain hamburger meat, if desired.
Mix all ingredients and simmer until desired thickness.
Serve hot over 1/2 of hamburger bun or bread.

title: surprise pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Crush crackers.
Add baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in crackers.
Add 1 cup of pecans and coconut.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Put topping on and sprinkle with pecans.

title: gourmet goulash
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and brown meat.
Add onions; lightly saute.
Stir in salt, pepper, flour and paprika.
Add wine, sour cream and tomato sauce, stirring to blend.
Turn mixture into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over boiled noodles.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick and shiny.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Cool to lukewarm. Once cool add strawberries, mix carefully until completely coated. Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate, serve with cool whip on top.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350°.
Let cool in pan.

title: hearty salmon fillets
directions: Arrange onion in bottom of greased 12-inch pan.
Place fish on top of onions.
Combine remaining vegetables and spread over the top of fish.

title: southern corn bread dressing(delicious)
directions: Toast day old light bread.
Corn bread, light bread, onion and celery are chopped in a food processor.
Add sage to these ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in sealable container and place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to cook, add eggs, melted margarine and stock.
Mixture should be soupy.
(Cake batter consistency.)
This is the secret of good dressing.
It will cook dry.

title: taylor's pizza meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a nine-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Pat meat into pie plate.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes.
Drain any liquid.
Top with sauce, cheese and vegetables.
Return to oven for five minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine and shape into 2-inch balls. Saute in 6 tablespoons butter until done. Drain, cool and freeze.
Makes 75 to 80 meatballs.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.

title: old fashion fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix well the salad oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon; add to mixture. Stir in nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Spread mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: dirt cups
directions: Note:
Will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper cups.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter until transparent.
Add meat; cook and stir.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and parsley; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream to heat. Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 standard loaf pans. Combine sugar, eggs and oil; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; add to mixture, then add apples. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mint flavored punch
directions: Combine sugar, mint and 2 cups boiling water; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Strain, reserving liquid; discard leaves. Stir together reserved liquid, grape juice, orange juice and lime juice.
Serve over crushed ice.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 13 (4 ounce) servings.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar until
light.
Add the slightly beaten eggs and mix well.
Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk or sour milk.
Add the flour and cinnamon to the sugar-egg mixture along with the soda-milk mixture.
Blend in the jam.
Bake in greased shallow baking pan 40 minutes at 325°.
Cut in squares and serve warm with butterscotch sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Put 1 cup pecans into each pie.
Press pecans into mixture with fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt irma's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after the addition of each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt, then add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Then add this mixture alternating with the butter mixture and liquids.
Add fruit that has been floured (but not out of the pound of flour) and the nuts.
Steam 4 hours, then run in oven to dry off.

title: rice-crusted ham 'n swiss pie
directions: Thoroughly combine rice, butter and 1 slightly beaten egg. Press lightly against sides and bottom of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
In rice crust, layer ham, cheese and 1/2 cup fried onions. Combine milk, remaining 2 eggs and pepper.
Pour over ham-cheese-onion filling.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: doris' seven-layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce into large serving bowl.
Over this, put peas, green pepper and onion.
Put mayonnaise on top, sealing edges well.
Sprinkle sugar on top and spread cheese evenly.
Add bacon, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meats with onions and garlic; drain.
Add tomato paste, Ragu and sauce mix.
Add sugar.
Season with oregano, basil and garlic powder to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the oil to water and boil lasagne according to package (1/2 box).
Mix softened cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream together. Layer half noodles, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Then lay chicken pieces on that.
Pour soups over chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in 4-quart ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: asian beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef, pour off fat and remove meat from pan. Season meat with 1 seasoning packet from Top Ramen.

title: spinach-filled mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems finely and saute with onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add spinach.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Add Swiss cheese, stirring lightly.
Remove from heat.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chop onion. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and mix. Bring to a boil a mixture of the remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, dry mustard, celery seed, salt, vinegar and oil. Pour dressing over slaw while still hot. Cool and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put cooked, flaked chicken in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crumble sleeve of Ritz crackers over chicken and slice stick of margarine over crackers.
Cook until bubbly and golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: old-fashioned noodle pudding
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in frying pan.
Add sliced apples. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar; stir until apples are completely coated.
Cover; cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour in pot.
Add milk and egg; stir over medium to high heat until thick.
Pour into premade pie shell.
Allow to cool.

title: indoor smores
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat the corn syrup, margarine and milk chocolate morsels just to boiling point, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal. Toss quickly until completely coated. Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press evenly in pan with buttered spoon.
Let stand 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: easy sauteed mushrooms
directions: Saute vegetables and garlic in butter 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in oregano, salt and pepper.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: fudge scotch squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in above order and mix well. Batter will be heavy. Press mixture into a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan. (A glass dish works well.) Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool before cutting into squares. Makes 25 servings.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup sugar and melted oleo. Pat into 2 pans leaving a little for garnish.
Chill Pet milk in freezer while preparing the following: Dissolve 1 cup boiling water.
Cream 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Remove Pet milk from freezer.
Whip milk until thick, then fold in Jell-O and cream cheese mixtures.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crusts and garnish with reserved crumbs.
Chill until set.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.
Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Use a layer of broccoli and a layer of buttered crumbs; bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: In a deep pie plate, stir together soup, oregano and water until smooth.
On waxed paper, combine crumbs and sesame seed.
On second sheet of waxed paper, place flour.
Coat chicken with flour, then soup mixture, then crumb mixture.
Place on wire rack in a jelly-roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: world's greatest meat loaf
directions: Beat egg lightly in bowl.
Add salt, pepper, thyme, basil, ketchup, mustard, bread crumbs and bouillon.
Mix well.
Mix in celery, onion and cheese.
Add ground meat and mix lightly.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: burnt almonds(brente mandler)
directions: Place almonds, sugar and water in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir.
Water will evaporate and the almonds will be dry. Keep stirring until sugar melts again and almonds are glazed with the caramelized sugar.
Pour on a cookie sheet to cool.
Separate while still warm with a fork dipped in oil.

title: crepes filled with laban
directions: Drain laban to make a sour cream cheese in a bag or colander. Chill.
Beat eggs and add salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter and add pine nuts.
Brown, drain well.
To the well drained laban, add drained pine nuts.
To make crepes, use small frying pan, heat with a little more butter.
Add dipper of eggs (2-3 tbsp.)
Spread around by moving around to edges.
Cook until lightly browned. Stack like pancakes.
To serve, use 1-2 tbsp. of filling for each crepe, then roll tightly.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour, beaten eggs, 7-Up and extract.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan 1 hour before removing.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and flavoring and beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Fold in nuts and pour in glass loaf pan.
Pour sauce over batter and bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: spoon tomato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, milk, and mushroom pieces together. Reserve half of it.
Put rice in the other half.
Place this mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in chicken.
Cover with reserved mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy one-dish ham or chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham or chicken and onion powder in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: onion slim dip
directions: Mix skim milk and cottage cheese in blender.
Blend on high until smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes.
Stir in onion soup mix. Chill 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix noodles, chicken, mayonnaise, celery, onion and bell peppers together with salt.
Set aside.
Mix soup and cheese. Heat together until cheese melts and mix with noodle mixture. Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix and marinate.
Let stand 1 to 2 days.

title: smoothie delight
directions: Legumes, which is another name for beans, peas and lentils, are all good sources of fiber, protein, iron, calcium, zinc and B vitamins.
This group also includes chickpeas, baked and refried beans, soy milk, tempeh and texturized vegetable protein.

title: honey ham tortilla rolls
directions: Beat ham and cream cheese.
Stir in pineapple, onion and honey.
Put 1/4 cup on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 3 to 8 hours before serving.
Slice each roll into 8 to 10 pieces.
Serve with dipping sauce made of 6 tablespoons mayonnaise, 1/4 cup mustard and 2 tablespoons honey.

title: chicken breasts almondine
directions: Wash chicken, drain and pat dry.
Rub with lemon juice; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rub with garlic, sprinkle with remaining seasonings and let stand for 3 hours.
Place broiler pan as far from heat as possible.
Place chicken on aluminum foil.
Dot with butter.
Broil in preheated broiler for 20 minutes on each side, basting frequently with butter.
Sprinkle with almonds 10 minutes before serving.
Serve topped with almonds and butter. Yields 2 servings.

title: mixed berry and cake delight
directions: Line a 2.5 qt bowl with plastic wrap; layer the slices of cake.
Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Pour 1 cup dissolved jello over the cake; cover completely.
Stir 2 cups dissolved jello into berries; until slightly thick.
Pour mixture over cake; covering completely.
Layer cake on top of berry mixture.
Pour remaining jello completely over cake.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from bowl and top with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Cook noodles.
Layer in large (9 x 13) casserole in this order:
hamburger/onion, 1/2 cup catsup, 1/2 of noodles, 3/4 teaspoon salt, 1/3 cup sliced olives, 1 cup tomato juice, 1 can mushroom soup, 1/4 pound grated Cheddar cheese. Repeat once with same quantities.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Great for a large group.
Also freezes well.

title: sand cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
In another bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Then mix pudding and creamed mixture together.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Melt the butter in the skillet.
Turn off the heat.
Crack the eggs into a mixing bowl.
Use a wire whisk to beat the mixture for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup milk to the eggs, then add the flour to egg mixture all at once, and use wooden spoon to beat mixture until smooth.
Beat in the remaining 1 1/2 cups milk, add the melted butter, salt and cinnamon.
Add the oil to the skillet. Drop about a tablespoon of the thin batter into the skillet for each pancake.

title: ruth's pecan refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix at night.
Place in pan with waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice thin either 1-inch square or oblong.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes and cool on waxed
paper. Excellent!
Keeps well either in tins or Ziplocs.

title: hot pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days prior to use.

title: brandied apples
directions: Slice pound cake and place on dessert plates. In saucepan, combine pie filling, allspice and brandy. Heat and stir just until heated thoroughly. Place several spoonfuls over cake. Top with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs on high for 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Combine flour and cocoa; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and cocoa dusted 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Frost with Cocoa Fudge frosting.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and allow to stand several hours or overnight.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place a stick of margarine in pan and place in warm oven.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in mixing bowl.
After margarine has melted, pour cobbler batter in pan, then pour in fruit.

title: stuffed beef round
directions: Cut steak into 6 serving size pieces.
Pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine cheese, onion, celery and parsley.
Place about 1/4 cup of cheese mixture in center of each piece of steak, reserving remaining cheese mixture (about 1 cup).
Roll up each steak, jelly roll fashion; secure with wooden picks or string.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place in order listed in 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan or baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana nut bread in a jar
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased loaf pan or jars at 350° until bread springs back when tested, about 45 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with bread stuffing; put in bottom of dish. Mix other ingredients together and put on top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce.
Makes 1 serving. Each serving counts as 1 fruit and 1/2 fat.

title: quiche - egg
directions: Whip cream.
Add ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat.
Bake 30 more minutes at 300°.
Let set for 10 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix together.
Divide into 2 crocks and bake in a 350° oven until thick, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon about every half hour.
Takes about 5 1/2 hours.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: curried rice-pilaf mix(gift idea)
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-cup jar with tight fitting lid.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Put cukes, onions, garlic and peppers in a bowl with cover. Place salt and celery on top; let stand, covered, one hour or more.
Mix vinegar and sugar into cucumbers.
Put in canning jars; lasts one month in fridge.
Can be used in one hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with 1 well-beaten egg (egg can be omitted during lent).
Mix well with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add margarine or butter and vanilla. Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thaw and drain peaches and strawberries. Add sliced bananas, pineapple and drained oranges.
Just before serving, fold in Cool Whip.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in raisins and combine egg, milk, pumpkin and melted butter.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Sprinkle with 2 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.
Freezes well.

title: orange fizz
directions: Combine orange juice and sugar; chill.
Put ice cubes in 4 glasses.
Add 1/4 cup mixture to each.
Fill glasses with ginger ale.
Stir gently.
Add orange slices for garnish.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Put all ingredients into slow cooker.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours or until thoroughly heated; stir once. Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Put milk and sugar into a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add toast, nuts and almond extract.
Mix until well blended.
Wet hands.
Shape almond mixture around cherries in the shape of a bell.
Roll bell in red or green sugar.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Makes about 50 bells.

title: best split pea soup
directions: Start early in the day.
In a large pot, put peas, water, bay leaf and salt; simmer, covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Saute onion, garlic, celery, potato and carrots in oil.
If necessary, add a little water to steam.
When tender, add to soup.
Continue simmering.
About 5 minutes before serving, add wine, mustard, thyme and sesame oil.
Just before serving, add vinegar, tomatoes and parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: bible fruit cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice as in Proverbs 23:14 and you should have good results.

title: wrapped caramels
directions: Cook slowly until soft ball forms at 240° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered pan; cool and cut into 3/4-inch squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slit open green chiles; remove seeds. Rinse and lay flat on paper towels to dry.
In medium bowl, whisk milk and flour with beaten egg.
Season batter with salt.
Layer half of chiles in bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with half of cheese and pour on half of batter.
Repeat with remaining chiles, cheese and batter.
Place in middle of oven. Bake 30 minutes.
Spoon mashed tomatoes evenly over top.
Bake 30 minutes longer, or until set.
Serves 4.

title: hominy
directions: Fry desired meat until brown; drain off fat.
Add hominy as you would potatoes.

title: rhubarb whip
directions: Cook the rhubarb, sugar and 1/4 cup water until tender.
Add the jello and 1/2 cup cold water.
Cool until thickened.
Whip the cream or some type of whipped topping.
Mix into rhubarb.
Chill until serving time.

title: awendaw seafood chowder
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat the oil and brown the potatoes, green bell pepper, onion, garlic and celery over medium heat.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, water, bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and carrots; simmer over low heat until the carrots are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add the clams, shrimp, lemon and parsley; cook until the clams and shrimp are cooked through, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot, in cups or bowls.
Yields 10 servings.

title: diet pizza
directions: Press biscuits into Pam sprayed pan.
Brush with egg white. Preheat oven to 400° and bake until brown.
Over this add 1/2 cup Ragu sauce, ground turkey, oregano, salt, onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Add another 1/4 cup Ragu sauce, Mozzarella cheese and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: miss donna's quick seafood corn chowder
directions: Heat potato soup and butter in saucepan.
Add milk, corn and seafood.
Season to taste with parsley, pepper and lots of Worcestershire.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in Bundt cake pan.

title: mary's rolls
directions: Put mashed potatoes into bowl; add shortening, sugar and scalded milk. When this mixture is tepid, add yeast which has been dissolved in the half cup of lukewarm water; add flour to make a medium stiff dough. Put this in the refrigerator to gradually rise until ready to make out the rolls.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients, only 1/2 at a time.
Mix all well together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch loaf pan in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut; add Cool Whip to each piece.

title: dr. pepper cake
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup Dr. Pepper and mix well.
Stir in 4 tablespoons cocoa, cinnamon and flour; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soda; beat until creamy.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° gas oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, melt remaining butter, cocoa and Dr. Pepper with vanilla; mix well.
Pour over hot cake.

title: squaw corn
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and green pepper; drain.
Cut tomatoes and add.
Add all ingredients but flour.
Bring to boil over medium heat, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Add flour to thicken. This is a meal in itself, very filling.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the lasagna as directed on box in a large skillet.
Heat pan with tomatoes.
Add chopped onion, chopped garlic and shredded carrots.
Cook for 5 minutes until light brown.
Then add ground beef and mix.
When beef is brown, pure the whole tomatoes after blending and add to the pan.
Add oregano, basil, butter, salt and pepper.
Half cover pan, simmer for 30 minutes.
Get a lasagna pan and put sauce on the bottom of it, put a layer of lasagna, Ricotta and half of the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add another layer of lasagna, Ricotta and the Parmesan cheese, and then cover sauce mixture over all.
Repeat process and then add another layer of noodles, sauces and sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: top of the stove rice pudding
directions: Place rice, milk, salt and sugar in a heavy saucepan; mix. Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Mix evaporated milk and eggs with beater.
Add to rice mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring rapidly to a rolling boil and turn off heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into Pyrex dish. Sprinkle liberally with nutmeg.
Let stand until set.
Chill.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Place cones in cupcake tins or bread pans.
Fill cones about 3/4 full with cake batter.
Bake according to package directions for cupcakes.
After the cones cool, frost with favorite frosting.
Add sprinkles, etc.
Fun for kids to help make.
Great for parties!

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage until leaves are loose.
Remove leaves.
Cut off hard veins on large leaves so they will roll easily.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put into casserole dish and top.

title: our favorite bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water 2 inches.
Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight; drain in the morning.
Add 2 quarts of water and ham bone or ham piece.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Add 1 large chopped onion and 1 can of tomatoes.
Season with chili powder, juice of lemon, salt and pepper.
Take out bone.
Cut up meat and return pieces to soup.
Simmer 1 hour or more.
Good with tossed salad and crackers.

title: sissy cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Mix in flour and vanilla. Spread in jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pound cake #5
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine together; add flavorings. Add
eggs one at a time, alternating with flour.
Start with flour and end with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in peach juice, heated to boiling point.
Then add ice cubes.
When mixture congeals slightly, add peaches and nuts.
Serves 8.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix spinach, eggs and butter.
Fold in flour and cheeses.
Mix well and place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookie crust pecan pie
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press dough over bottom and 3/4-inch up sides of pan.
In medium bowl, combine pudding mix, pecans, syrup, milk and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch. Over medium heat, boil together 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O. Stir until completely dissolved. Add lemon juice.
Stir and cool. When cooled, add about 1 quart sliced strawberries.
Pour into pie crust and set in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Garnish with extra strawberries, if desired.

title: taco sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion over medium-high heat; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer 1 to 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Place 5 biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet; press each biscuit into 5-inch circle.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each flattened biscuit.
Press or roll remaining biscuits into 5-inch circles.
Place over meat mixture.
Press with a fork to seal.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Top with salsa and sour cream.
Garnish with lettuce.

title: brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare brownie mix according to cake instructions. Pour in cake pan. Bake 16 to 18 minutes or until done. Do not overbake. Layer coconut and chocolate chunks over top of brownies. Pour the condensed milk evenly over mixture onto the top and sprinkle with almonds. Bake 20 to 23 minutes or until coconut is golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together oil and honey.
Add eggs, vanilla and zucchini; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture; stir in nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack and cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift together all ingredients 3 times.
Store in air tight container.

title: crispix
directions: Boil the oleo, brown sugar and syrup for 2 minutes. Meanwhile, put Crispix in heavy brown paper bag.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/4 syrup mixture over Crispix.
Close bag and shake; microwave it for 1 minute.
Do this 3 more times until all mixture is used. Pour in flat pan to cool.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding and milk until thick.
Add cake mix (dry) to hot pudding and stir with spoon until mixed well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Add small can chow mein noodles on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add sour milk with baking soda dissolved in it.
Stir in flour (sifted) with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or frost.

title: winter sherbet
directions: Combine pineapple and peaches in electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Pour mixture into 9-inch square pan.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Freeze until almost firm, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Return mixture to pan and freeze until firm. Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 1 quart.

title: shrimp 'n rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix shrimp, rice, celery, olives, pepper and onion; cover and chill.
Just before serving, mix salt, pepper and mayonnaise; toss with shrimp mixture.
Spoon mixture on crisp greens; garnish with tomato wedges.
Serve with French dressing and lemon wedges.

title: oven stew
