directions: Mix soups and water well.
Add meat, carrots and potatoes. Put into casserole or pan and cover.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: swiss chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter apples (stems, seeds, peelings and all) in deep pot. Add apple juice to cover. Cook until soft and run through sieve. Measure and add sugar 4 to 1 (4 cups apples to 1 cup sugar).
Add cinnamon and cook slowly until apple butter.

title: crab mold
directions: Put the water, gelatine and cream of mushroom soup in a double boiler.
Melt and stir until hot.
Take off the heat and add rest of the stuff.
Cut crabmeat, onions and celery small, about bite sizes.
Pour into mold pan and chill overnight!
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine the
oat bran, nuts, raisins and baking powder; stir in brown sugar.
Mix the milk, egg whites and oil together and blend
with
the oat bran mixture.	Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.
They
should
be	moist but not wet.
Makes 12 muffins. Store in
plastic
bag
to retain moisture.
Keep in the refrigerator.
This
recipe is for those who have to watch their cholesterol levels.

title: beef brisket with cabbage
directions: Pour enough cold water in a large casserole; enough to cover the meat.
Add the onion and the garlic.
Boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 2 hours.
Remove beef and keep warm.
Skim fat from broth.
Add cabbage.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
When ready, cut the meat and garnish with cabbage on a large platter.
Serves 4.

title: special "k" treats
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until sugar is dissolved; then add Special K cereal, 2 cups at a time, and stir gently.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then melt the last ingredients.
Pour over treats and let set at least 10 minutes.
Cut into desired pieces.

title: easy quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and add onion and green pepper. Saute until medium soft.
Put in glass pie plate. Pour over eggs, milk, cheese, etc.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400°
for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Mix soup, cheese and vegetable liquid.
Add broccoli and stir.
Pour mixture in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine grape gelatin and hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add crushed pineapple with juice and blueberry pie filling to gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill in refrigerator until set.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cut chicken in strips; stir-fry in 1 to 2 tablespoons oil, until no longer pink.
Remove.
Stir-fry all vegetables 3 to 4 minutes, until just tender (crisp).
Add gravy, soy sauce and ginger, then add meat and heat.
Last, add the pineapple chunks. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: swiss cheese broccoli
directions: Put in boiling water for 5 minutes. Rinse under cold water.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together; store in tight container.
Just add to 1 cup hot water when serving.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Slit back of shrimp shell, remove black vein, cut part way through and wash shrimp.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well, either by hand or wooden spoon.
Stuff shrimp and bake on greased baking sheet in 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4. Can be served with additional melted butter and fresh lemon.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Spray an 8 or 9 inch pan with cooking spray.
Mix the jello with and water in a bowl and microwave for about 1 1/2 minute. Stir to dissolve.
Add marshmallows, microwave for 1 minute or until marshmallows are almost melted.
Stir slowly until the mixture is smooth.
The creamy layer will float to the top.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set. Starting at one end, roll up the gelatin tightly with seam side down.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add beaten eggs one at a time.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat.
Fill muffin-sized paper baking cups to 1/8 inch from top.
Baking time, 1 hour; temperature, 350°.
Serves 30.
Remove from oven after baking and let cool.
On indentation on top of cupcake is to be filled with cherry pie filling or filling of your choice.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Put raisins into a saucepan.
Add water and bring to a boil. Boil for three minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Do not drain.
Mix flour with other dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in raisins with vanilla; gradually add the flour mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet in large spoonfuls.
Bake in oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Brown sausage and drain all excess fat.
In a skillet, combine sausage, onion, celery, spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer until celery and onions are tender.
Add green peppers and mushrooms and simmer until peppers are tender and sauce is thickened.
Serve sausage and vegetables over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon and soda; "set aside".
Beat oil, eggs and sugar.
Gradually add dry ingredients until moistened. Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together Marshmallow Creme, cream cheese, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with fresh fruit: strawberries, kiwi, melons, pineapple, etc.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers.
In a bowl, combine sour cream, onion, lemon juice, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add cucumbers and mix well. Chill for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple bowl
directions: Cut crown from pineapple about 2 inches down from top.
Remove core and hollow out fruit with a sharp knife.
Soften cheese with cream cheese.
Fold in chopped pineapple; return to shell and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs, and egg whites.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Form dough into small balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mini pizza
directions: Brown sausage, set aside. Melt cheese. Add sausage, ketchup, Worcestershire, and oregano to melted cheese and mix together. Spread mix on Party Rye bread and place in oven and broil to melt spread.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and water. Beat until mixed.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls. Bake at 325°.

title: cow patty
directions: Press softened cream cheese onto large round plate or tray. Sprinkle taco sauce seasoning on top.
Spread bean dip on next. Spoon on picante sauce.
Layer remaining ingredients ending with cheese.
Serve with dip chips.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain some juice from pineapple.
Mix remaining pineapple with juice, flour and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese on top of pineapple mixture.
Crumble crackers and add on top of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl beat eggs and gradually add sugar until well mixed.
Add the vegetable oil and beat.
Mix together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to the egg, sugar and oil mixture together with zucchini in small amounts. Alternate first dry and then zucchini.
Add walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Freezes well for future use.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with 3 tablespoons salsa. Spread on an ungreased pie plate. Combine remaining 3 tablespoons of salsa with the cocktail sauce. Layer it. Layer remaining ingredients along with chopped onions.

title: cobbler
directions: First, melt butter in bottom of pan for pie.
Then mix sugar, flour, milk and salt; pour into buttered pan.
Add the fruit and bake.
It will make its own crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or about.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in pie pan or small casserole dish.
Combine sugar and cheese; sprinkle on top.
Crush crackers, mix with butter and sprinkle on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: instant pie
directions: Bring the water, cornstarch and sugar to a boil.
Add 1 box instant jello and boil again.
Crumble 1 angel food cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the Dream Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Layer strawberries and glaze onto top and repeat layer. Top with strawberries.

title: banana muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix bananas, sugar and oil together well. Add vanilla, brown rice flour, baking soda and xanthan gum; mix well. Pour into regular size or mini muffin pans and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Put the tray on the table for the pizza.
Put the rest of the stuff on the pizza.
Put it in a 400° oven for 6 hours.
When the timer beeps, the pizza is done.
Take it out and eat it for dinner.

title: yellow cake
directions: Sift together flour
and sugar; add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat	2
minutes at medium speed.
Add rest of milk and eggs.
Beat
2	minutes more.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch
pans.	Bake
at
350°	for
to 40 minutes.
Use coconut frosting.

title: banana bread
directions: Squish bananas, eggs, oil and vanilla together well.
Sift flour with sugar, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Pour batter into greased and waxed paper lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Or greased muffin pans 3/4 full at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oyster soup
directions: Drain oysters.
Add them to butter or margarine and cook 3 minutes or until edges curl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Bring almost to boiling point.
Serves 6.

title: daddy's pimento cheese
directions: Put cheese in food processor with regular chopping blade and process until fine pieces.
Add pimentos and juice, salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Add about 1 cup mayonnaise and mix well. Mixture should not be soupy or stiff.
Add more mayonnaise, if needed, to get desired consistency.
It should move from one side of container to the other when tilted.
Take out of refrigerator a few minutes before serving to soften.

title: bill's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain off grease.
Put tomatoes, beans, tomato juice and seasonings in large pan.
Now add hamburger and onion mixture.
Let simmer for several hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, beaten eggs and milk.
Blend flour into mixture.
Roll into small balls and press down with a fork in the pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Place apples in a greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and apple cider; pour over apples. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with nuts or raisins.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm over ice cream. Yields 4 servings.

title: venison short ribs
directions: Soak venison in salt water overnight.
Wash ribs and boil about 30 minutes in a pressure cooker at 10 pounds pressure. Remove the ribs to a baking dish, mix the remaining ingredients and pour this over them.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hanky pankin' party ryes
directions: Brown ground meat and sausage with spices.
Drain.
Set aside. Cube Velveeta cheese and melt; either in the microwave or on the stove with the meat.
Mix ingredients together.
Spread on cocktail rye.
Flash freeze for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake on a cookie sheet approximately 6 to 8 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients by hand.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: filled hot buns
directions: Put through food chopper and fill the buns.
Heat 20-30 min. at 275°.

title: fruited yogurt pie
directions: *Use
light yogurt for diabetics and restricted calorie diets. Use diet whip topping also.

title: mexican flan
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt 2 c. sugar in saucepan over low heat, cooking until golden, stirring continuously for 5 to 8 minutes.
Watch sugar carefully as it can burn quickly.
Put the caramel into custard cups to cover the bottoms.
In mixing bowl, add remaining sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Boil the milk, then slowly add to sugar-egg mixture, whisking well.
Strain through a fine strainer.
Ladle the mixture into the caramel coated custard cups, filling 3/4 full.
Put the filled cups into a water bath and cover.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
To serve, run a knife around edges, loosen and invert on to plates.

title: aunt nannie's squash loaf
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in loaf pan or casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, rub in the butter.
Make into a very wet dough with buttermilk or well soured milk.
Knead lightly.
Put in a greased 7-inch cake tin.
Make a cross on top with a floured knife.
Cover with a lid and bake in a 375-400 degree oven for about 30-45 minutes.
Dark, crumbly and delicious.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
In saucepan, mix soup and mayonnaise. Bring to a boil.
Place 1/3 cup corn flake crumbs in bottom of casserole. Add cabbage.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage. Cover with 2/3 cup corn flake crumbs and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate Kisses in large bowl.
Mix on lowest speed until dough forms. Shape into balls, using rounded teaspoonful for each cookie.
Roll in granulated sugar; place on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a chocolate Kiss and press so cookie cracks around base.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add spices and egg and beat well. Dissolve soda in a little warm water and add applesauce. Combine the two mixtures. Add the flour in which raisins and other fruit have been dredged. Bake in a greased loaf pan 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven. Line bottom of pan with waxed paper for easier removal from pan.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Scramble meat with onion and seasoning to taste; drain well. Mix cheese soup and tomatoes; add meat.
Heat in microwave until good and hot.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer; beat until smooth.
Chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: candy
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients on low heat, then remove from stove and add marshmallows.
Spread in pan and when set, cut into squares.

title: janet's glazed ham with dijon pineapple sauce
directions: Score ham, stud with cloves and cherries.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, syrup and mustard.
Use 3/4 cup glaze mixture to baste ham every 10 minutes during the last 35 to 40 minutes of baking.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check at 45 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Mix in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Top with favorite fruit.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over grated cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Put chopped celery and pepper over and leave 20 minutes.
Drain well. Mix vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, mustard and celery seed; bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Let stand until cool.
Pack into containers (not full).
Freeze. Delicious.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix coconut and butter; press into pie pan.
Brown in oven at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Prepare coconut cream pudding; sit in refrigerator until set, then mix with Cool Whip.
Turn into prepared pie pan.
Chill pie.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Cook eggs in separate pot.
Dice onion, pickles, olives and eggs.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, add enough mayonnaise and mustard to coat.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add sugar and shortening to hot water and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup of warm water, then add this to the sugar mixture.
Add the beaten eggs and 3 cups of flour.
Mix well with hands, then put on board and knead well.
(Probably will take about 2 cups of flour.)
Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in greased pan to rise for about 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken pie quick and easy
directions: Simmer chicken breasts about 1 hour in a covered pan with celery salt, lemon juice and about 1 1/2 cups water.
When tender, drain (reserving broth) and remove skin and bones.
Chop into large pieces.
In an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, pour soup and thin with 1/2 cup of the broth.
Season with salt and pepper; stir in chicken pieces.
Top with roll dough (unrolled, but not separated).
Dough need not meet exactly in center or on sides. Bake at 375° until crust is brown and filling is bubbling (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in greased casserole or Pyrex loaf pan.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese stollen
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Place it in middle of roll.
Fold over and seal edges.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and shrimp casserole
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery; saute in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover; cook in microwave on High for 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of three 9-inch pans with waxed paper.
Microwave chocolate and water in large bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
Gently stir into batter. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Remove from oven; immediately run spatula between cake and sides of pan.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove from pans; peel off waxed paper.
Cool on wire racks.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage; drain.
Remove 1/2 of the sausage and set aside.
Stir tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and brown sugar into sausage; simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine remaining sausage, Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg and parsley.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Whip until smooth. Refrigerate.

title: nutty wild rice
directions: In skillet, saute pecans in butter until lightly toasted. Add celery and saute about 3 minutes longer. Add rice, parsley and garlic salt. Cook until heated through, stirring constantly.

title: fruit salad basket
directions: Lay a dampened dish towel on a counter or table and place melon on top to prevent it from rolling.
With a water soluble marker, draw outline of basket onto melon, making sure the handle is at
least 1 1/4 inches wide.
Using a large sharp knife, carefully cut melon along marker line.
Remove excess rind and set aside.
With a melon baller, scoop out all the watermelon flesh and place in a large glass or ceramic bowl; set aside.
With a vegetable peeler, even out scalloped edges of watermelon.
Cover watermelon basket with clear plastic wrap and set aside. With a melon baller, scoop out flesh from cantaloupes and honeydews.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, lime juice, lemon juice and lime peel.
Stir well.
Add all melon balls, strawberries and grapes; toss to combine.
Allow fruit to chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, transfer fruit salad to watermelon basket.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar or glaze with orange frosting.

title: freselles
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each part to resemble large bread sticks (about 2-inches wide).
Can be made smaller.
Slice off in 1/2-inch pieces and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.

title: happy time punch
directions: Combine frozen concentrate and water.
Place sherbet, ice cream and small amount of juices in bottom of punch bowl.
Add rest of juices.
Stir until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted. Makes 6 quarts.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in medium skillet. Drain fat. In a separate bowl, mix together soup and milk. Add beef and onion to soup mixture. Stir. Layer Tater Tots on bottom of 2-quart baking dish (or 9 x 13 pan). Pour beef and soup mixture over top of Tater Tots. Top with remaining Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into large zipper bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 9 cups.

title: hot water pastry
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour water over shortening and mix with fork until creamy.
Add flour mixture and mix into a dough.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 1 (9-inch) double crust.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix margarine and flour until dough forms.
Add chopped nuts. Put in oblong casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Put a layer of this mixture on crust.
Layer with pudding mixture, then layer of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Marinate roast in mixture of last 6 ingredients for 2 to 3 days, turning at least once a day.
Cook, uncovered, with marinade in Dutch oven at 250° for 45 minutes for rare or up to 2 hours for well done.
Can be served hot or cold, with or without marinade on side.
Great for buffets.

title: judy's favorite pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in the refrigerator to chill.
(I mix this in a Tupperware bowl that has a built in colander so it doesn't get too sloppy.)

title: manzetta
directions: Brown beef, add onion
and
pepper (saute), drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Add cooked spaghetti with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken country captain
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Place skin side up in foil-lined pan (9 x 13-inch works well).
Brown onion and green peppers in oil.
Add garlic, thyme, curry, stewed tomatoes and sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve on rice.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling liquid.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle cookie crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
In large bowl add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add egg and mix until well blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and transfer cheesecake to serving platter.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.

title: pastry made with oil
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Measure
oil and milk into measuring cup. Add to flour and
stir with fork until mixture forms a ball. Divide in half and
roll
between two sheets of waxed paper. Makes two crusts.
Bake
at
450° for ten minutes when recipe calls for use of baked pie shell.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In large iron skillet, melt margarine; add brown sugar and let melt into margarine.
Place pineapple rings around sides and middle of skillet.
Put cherries in center of each pineapple ring. Mix cake as directed on box and pour over pineapple rings.
Bake at 370° until a toothpick comes out of cake clean.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Take package of jello.
Add hot water as directed and stir. Add ice cream.
Stir.
Put in mold or bowl and refrigerate.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend corn, egg, flour, salt and pepper together. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and let cook until golden brown.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Place croutons and cheese in the bottom of a greased 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.
Serve immediately.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese and spices. Stir until cheese melts.
Spread on bread slices.
Freezes well. When ready to serve, bake at 350° until hot.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.	Bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 35 to 40 minute at 350°.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, two at a time, and beat for 5 minutes after each addition of eggs, using medium speed.
Pour into baked pie shell.
(I use pre-packaged chocolate crumb.)
Place in refrigerator.
After it sets, top with whipped cream, chopped nuts and chocolate shavings.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cook squash until soft in salt seasoned water and drain. Mash.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: friendship cake(30 day)
directions: Must use "starter" or make own.
Use fruit cocktail if you are just beginning.
Let stand covered 10 days after adding 1 cup sugar.
Let stand at room temperature.
Stir every day.
After 10 days you are ready to begin.
1st Day:
Mix together the 1 1/2 cups starter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 can peaches.
Keep covered in large container at room temperature.
Stir every day.

title: kottia's favorite cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in a large saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and add oats.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Drain excess liquid.
Place pecans on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven, place pecans on another cookie sheet.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Let pecans cool and remove from cookie sheet.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake in an 18 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan or divide cake batter into 2 (13 x 9-inch) cake pans.

title: milk shakes and malts
directions: Put all ingredients into Osterizer blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until smooth.

title: my chinese candy
directions: Melt first two ingredients in double boiler just to smoothness.
Stir in noodles and marshmallows.
Spoon drop onto wax paper.
Refrigerate to set.
Great taste!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, dry milk, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add eggs, warm water and corn oil. Add cream cheese, jalapeno peppers, onion and cheese. Cook at 425° for 30 minutes in 2 well-greased pans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: new maraschino cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Add shortening, cherry juice, milk and cherries. Beat 2 minutes add egg white unbeaten. Beat for 2 minutes fold in nuts. Grease and flour 13 X 9 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes if using layer pans or 35-40 minutes if using 13 X 9.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs and eggs with 1 cup tomato sauce; reserve remaining sauce.
Mix in onion, green pepper and seasonings. Shape mixture into loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over top of loaf; continue baking 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: irene's chocolate fudge
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring continuously sugar, milk, chocolate and Karo.
When reaches a hard-boiled stage, remove from heat and add oleo, vanilla and pecans.
Beat or stir vigorously until begins to harden.
Pour out onto buttered plate.
Cut.

title: grape jelly fruit cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well, add eggs, one at a time, then jelly,
cinnamon,
nutmeg, allspice, melted charlotte and orange paste, sift
flour	and
baking powder.
Roll fruits in 1/2 cup flour, add flour
1 cup at a time, add fruit and flour and vanilla.
Bake
slowly
hours or until done.
When tested, pour wine
over
cake.
When cold, put in a container, cut raw apple on
top, add spoonfuls of wine over it, then put a tight lid over it, for two to three weeks before Christmas.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread into 9 x 5-inch pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sangria
directions: Into large pitcher, pour juices and sugar.
Stir to dissolve. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 6 cups punch or 8 (6 ounce) servings.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Parboil zucchini until just fork tender.
Cool.
Meanwhile, brown sausage and onion.
Drain off fat.
Cut zucchini lengthwise. Scoop out and discard seeds.
Scoop out pulp, almost to rind.
Add pulp to sausage, along with cracker crumbs, thyme, eggs and Mozzarella.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toss lightly.
Place in covered bowl and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
This will keep for a week or more.

title: waurine's frozen pineapple salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugars. Stir in yogurt and drained pineapple.
Spoon into 10 paper muffin cups and place in muffin pan.
Combine pecans and cherries and place atop each cup.
Cover.
Freeze firm.
Let stand for about 10 minutes before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Spoon on hot greased griddle and bake until bubbles appear.
Turn and bake.

title: shrimp loaf
directions: Remove filling out of bread.
Mix with ingredients and put mixture back in bread loaf.
Roll lightly in foil and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: no-knead yeast rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, mix the 2 cups of flour and yeast with a wooden spoon.
Put milk, butter, sugar and salt into saucepan. Cook and stir on medium heat until butter melts and mixture is warm (115°).
Pour warm mixture over flour mixture and add egg. Beat at low speed with mixer for 30 seconds.
Gradually stir in the 1 1/4 cups of all-purpose flour.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Grease waxed paper with some shortening.
Cover dough in bowl with the waxed paper.
Put in a warm place to rise for
1 hour or until dough is twice as big.
Beat dough with a wooden spoon.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Grease 20 muffin pans, filling them about halfway.
Cover with greased waxed paper and let rise 30 minutes or until twice as big.
About 10 minutes before time is up, turn oven up to 400°.
Remove waxed paper and put pans in oven.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove rolls from oven and serve warm.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and juice with 2 cups water.
Boil for 5 minutes or until sugar is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining water and cool.
Just before serving, add ice.
Garnish with lemon slices and mint (if desired).

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Combine crab meat, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise in 1 1/2-quart casserole; mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; stir until blended. (Mixture will be stiff.)
Spoon into generously buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until browned and slightly puffed.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork.
Place in saucepan.
Gradually beat in water and apple juice.
Add cinnamon sticks and cloves. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Serve hot.
Garnish with orange or lime slices. Makes approximately 2 quarts.
Can put in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon flour, 1/2 cup sugar and water together and add apples.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, oatmeal, 1/2 cup flour, cinnamon and salt.
Crumble with margarine.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Stir milk, soup, vinegar and garlic into bacon drippings and heat.
Combine soup mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Can divide ingredients into 2 separate bowls with covers and freeze one.
Bake other one at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan, combine pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to box directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt butter and cream cheese together, stir in powdered sugar and pour over batter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: rhubarb 'n dumplings(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine brown and white sugars, cornstarch, 3 tablespoons oleo and water.
Add rhubarb. Micro-cook, uncovered, on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every minute.
Cover casserole to keep warm.

title: 5 hour no peek stew
directions: Layer all ingredients in crock-pot; sprinkle cornstarch over stew.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in greased pie plate.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and place in a mixing bowl.
Soften butter to room temperature and blend in with cheese.
Add flour, celery powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and white pepper.
Mix well to form a stiff dough.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Blend in blender enough green tomatoes for 3 cups of paste. Measure in cooking kettle.
Add sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes. Remove from burner.
Add red Jell-O and stir good.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: berry pie
directions: Melt butter in deep baking pan.
Pour on top of it a batter made with the sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Have ready the fruit heated with extra sugar.
Pour the hot fruit on top of batter.
Bake in 370° oven for 25 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt stick margarine in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: vanilla rings(vanilluhringir)
directions: Chop the flour, sugar and vanilla with the butter directly on baking table.
Add egg yolk and work the dough together.
Put the dough in a cold place to stiffen.
Pipe the dough into strips. Shape them into rings.
Put onto greased baking sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 200°C (360°F).

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute vegetables (except carrots) with bacon and add to cooked potatoes.
(When you boil potatoes, cook a very short time, so they don't mush.)
Add corn, butter and milk last, do not boil after adding milk, it will curdle.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Flatten out crescent dough.
Spread with sausage and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll up and chill until very firm, but not frozen.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Beat cocoa and water until smooth. Add sugar and Karo.
Boil until you have a soft ball. Remove from heat, add both milks, vanilla and salt. Keep in refrig. Makes 2 qts.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into patties.
Fry in Crisco or Wesson oil until golden brown on both sides for 2 to 3 minutes each side.

title: slow cooker lasagna
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add the tomato sauce, water, tomato paste, salt and oregano; mix well.
Spread a fourth of the meat sauce in an ungreased 5-quart slow cooker.

title: vanilla wafer goodies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into round balls or oblong cookies and roll in coconut.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place pork chops in 3-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover and microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn meat over during cooking.
Drain. Mix together potatoes, onions, cheese, flour, salt and pepper. Layer over pork chops.
Dot with butter and pour milk over top. Cover and microwave on Defrost for 45 to 60 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: To corn, add salt, pepper, flour and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (tomatoes, cukes and onions according to your taste) in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight at least.
Keeps about 2 weeks in refrigerator if you can keep it that long.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Rub ginger over steaks and sprinkle with garlic salt or fresh garlic.
Marinate steaks about 1 hour prior to cooking.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Pour broccoli and rice over butter while hot. Mix other ingredients together with broccoli-rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: hummingbird cake or muffins
directions: Mix lightly together; do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or 30 minutes for muffins.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to the directions on the box using a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
Poke holes in the cake as soon as you take it out of the oven.
Heat the two ice cream toppings (if needed) and pour them over the holes in the cake.
Let the cake cool completely in the refrigerator.
After it has cooled, top it with the Cool Whip and break the candy bars into very small pieces and spread over the Cool Whip.

title: green bean hamburger pie
directions: Brown the onion in fat until done.
Add beef, salt and pepper.
Drain the green beans and mix with 1 can tomato soup.
Add the meat mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook potatoes until done.
Mash potatoes with 1/2 cup milk and 1 egg.
Spoon potatoes on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and bread dip
directions: Cut out center of bread into a "boat."
Pull bread apart into dipping pieces and place around "boat."
Mix all ingredients together and chill for 2 hours before filling "boat."

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat in.
Add flour and vanilla.
Place nuts in well greased floured pan and pour batter over nuts.
(Dab spoonfuls of dough over nuts and spread as evenly as possible.)
Dice pineapple and cherries and press down into the batter.
Bake at 350° about 45 mins. in 13x9-inch pan. Cool and cut into bars.
(I use less pecans.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs and soup well.
Add broccoli.
Grease shallow baking dish.
Pour mixed ingredients in baking dish and cover with 1/2 cup soft shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: bulgarian salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together for the dressing. Heat until dissolved. After it is cool, pour over vegetables and serve. This will keep in the fridge for up to 2 weeks, so you can enjoy as a side dish with supper or a healthy snack.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Remove from oven and spread miniature marshmallows on top of crust.
Return to oven until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from oven.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Put in oven immediately.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.
Remove from oven and empty onto a wire rack and brush melted oleo all over the sides, top and bottom.

title: shrimp wine scampi
directions: Clean shrimp.
Melt butter.
Add garlic and wine.
Place shrimp on flameproof platter or large broiling pan.
Pour garlic-wine butter over shrimp; season with salt and pepper. Place in preheated broiler 3 inches from heat; broil 5 to 10 minutes, until shrimp turn pink, turning once.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: maple twists
directions: Sift flour with baking powder; set aside.
Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, milk and flavorings.
Mix in flour mixture.
Divide in 5 parts, roll thin, spread with melted margarine and sprinkle with brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Fold toward center.
Cut in strips and twist.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir together green beans, soup and seasonings.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with onions before completely baked.

title: kolach (nut strudel)(yield:  5 strudels)
directions: Mix yeast with lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Cream shortening; add 1/2 cup sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add yeast mix and salt; mix well.
Add flour alternately with condensed milk with 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Knead dough until it stops sticking to fingers.
Divide into five equal portions.
Roll about 1/4 inch thick on floured surface.
Spread filling over dough.
Roll up and brush top with melted margarine. Put in greased pan, set in warm place for 1 hour and let rise. Bake at 375° until nice and brown.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve ingredients; then add 1 cup cold water.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Gets hard in about 1 hour.
Cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.
Let kids use their fingers to eat them.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a small glass bowl, combine garlic, lime juice, olive oil, herbs and seasonings.
Add chicken breasts; toss to coat with mixture and marinate until ready to cook.
Over medium heat, preheat stir-fry pan.
Add olive oil, garlic and jalapeno.
Cook briefly.
Add onion slices and bell pepper strips.
Toss to coat with oil and cook until onion becomes translucent.
Vegetables will still be slightly crisp.
Remove from heat and reserve. Preheat grill or broiler. Remove chicken breasts from marinade and place on grill or under broiler.
Grill until just done, turning once.
Baste with marinade.
Slice into thin strips.
Season with salt.
Preheat fajita pan under broiler or on top of stove until very hot.
Remove and coat with oil.
Place onion-pepper mixture on one side of pan and chicken slices on the other.
The ingredients will begin to sizzle.
Serve immediately with tortillas, guacamole, sour cream and salsa.

title: moist corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Stir ingredients and pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until smooth and fluffy.
Gradually add Key lime juice.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
(A chocolate crust is good too.)
Top with Cool Whip. Make a day ahead, it's better.
Also can freeze until ready for use.

title: low-sodium puffy omelet(serves 6; under 200 calories)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks in separate bowl with water, paprika, Angostura and pepper.
Pour into egg whites, folding in gently, until well blended.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture evenly into pie crusts, chill.
Whip cream until stiff.
Blend in pineapple and nuts.
Spoon on top of chilled egg mixture and chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 pies.
This is very rich.

title: john garner eggs
directions: Mix together 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Cover bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch glass baking dish with the 1/4 pound sliced cheese.
Cover with one half the cream mixture.
Break 10 eggs over this.
Cover with remaining cream mixture.

Sprinkle grated cheese over the top. Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and eggs set; or cover with Saran and hold in refrigerator uncooked. For morning guests, bring to room temperature, uncover and bake.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except milk, marshmallows, red and green cherries and nuts.
In double boiler put the evaporated milk and marshmallows; melt together.
Add to graham cracker mixture.
Press into well-greased 3-quart round casserole dish.
Place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Decorate the top of cake with alternate rows of red and green cherries and row of walnuts or pecans.

title: fruit salad
directions: Bring juice to a boil and add vanilla pudding and tapioca pudding.
Boil about 1 minute.
Cool.
Add fruit.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Line a 12 x 8-inch buttered baking dish with bread slices. Layer sausage on top of this, then layer of cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and seasonings; pour over above.
Refrigerate overnight or long enough for it to set up.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Simmer carrots in water until almost tender.
Remove carrots and add juice and sorghum to carrot water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and let stand.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lime-seasoned salmon
directions: Rinse salmon; pat dry.
Combine remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl; brush over salmon.
Place salmon in a greased grill basket (or directly on the grill, if you do not have one).
Grill until salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork, brushing often with the sauce.
Turn halfway through grilling.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, oregano and milk, just until blended.
Turn into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake a la gooch
directions: Cream together the margarine, shortening, sugar and the flavorings.
Add to the cream 6 eggs, one at a time, thoroughly beating the mixture after adding each egg.
Finally, to mixture, add 1 cup of milk and 3 cups of flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into tube pan.
Place in cold oven and turn oven on to 350°.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes; remove and serve hot.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Heat griddle to 350°.
Mix muffin mix, milk, oil and eggs until blended.
For each pancake, pour less than 1/4 cup batter onto griddle.
Cook 1/2 to 2 minutes or until golden; flip over on other side.
Cook until golden brown.
Yields about ten 4-inch pancakes.

title: jutta's rouladen
directions: Dice bacon and fry until almost crisp.
Add finely chopped onion and continue frying until onion is transparent.
Drain fried onion and bacon thoroughly and set aside.
Lay slices of the top round on flat surface.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on both sides. Spread slices of meat with a little mustard.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of bacon-onion mixture over beef rolls.
Roll meat up in jelly roll like fashion and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown rouladen in hot fat on all sides.
Add about 1 1/2 tablespoons of flour and add approximately 2 to 3 cups of water for gravy.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, bouillon cube and Knorr all-purpose seasoning.
Serve with homemade spatzle (homemade noodles), rice or mashed potatoes.

title: phyl's coconut cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Add shortening and 2/3 milk; beat 2 minutes. Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla; beat 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. As soon as cake comes from oven, punch holes and pour 1 can cream of coconut over it.

title: becky's favorite jello salad
directions: Mix lime and lemon jello with hot water.
Let stand.
In appropriate jello mold or container, mix the remaining ingredients.
Add jello.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until done.
Set chicken aside.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together in ovenproof dish.
Add more chopped onion to the top.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Heat through in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with Doritos or Fritos chips.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef; then add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and sprinkle herb stuffing over top.
Bake in a casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham-pecan-blue cheese pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese, tossing well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately or chill, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in baking dish or pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Put chicken, skin side down, with seasonings.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove chicken, put rice, onion and green pepper into pan over drippings.
Replace chicken, skin side up, pour chicken broth over chicken, rice, etc.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 400° or until rice has soaked up broth and chicken is tender.

title: peanut butter - chocolate chip - oatmeal cookies
directions: Add flour and baking soda; set aside.
Cream eggs, oleo, sugar and vanilla; beat in peanut butter.
Add flour mixture, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: french market soup
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Drain beans.
Place in crock-pot with 2 quarts water and ham hock.
Add celery, chicken, sausage, thyme, parsley and bay leaves.
Cook on high for 1 hour. Reduce to low and cook for 6 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar with margarine.
Stir in milk. Add flour, salt, baking powder, 4 tablespoons cocoa and pecans. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and 2/3 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Mix vanilla in boiling water. Pour over batter.
Do not stir!
It is best to put pan in oven before pouring water over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nutty white chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
In medium bowl combine flour, soda and salt. mix well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.
In large bowl with an electric mixer blend sugars at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste, scraping down the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat at medium speed until fully combined.
Add the flour mixture, pecans and white chocolate, blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tbsp onto ungreased cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake 20-22 minutes or until edges begin to turn golden brown.
Use a spatula to transfer cookies immediately to a cool, flat surface.
Yields: 3 dozen.

title: mary's four layer dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour and margarine with pastry blender.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Drain and grind
prunes.
Mix as you would any cake, adding nuts last.
Bake in a bread pan at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: standing rib roast
directions: In morning, preheat oven to 375°.
Roast one hour; turn oven off.
Do not open oven door.
Before serving, reheat roast at 375° for one hour.

title: sauce for stir-fry
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Pour over stir-fry.

title: summertime cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Boil to a very soft ball.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix; chill; serve with fresh veggies or chips.

title: mom's sunday salad
directions: Set aside jello, boiling water and cold water to jell.
When it starts to set, add cottage cheese, pineapple and Dream Whip. Put in pretty glass bowl.
Let set completely and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Good on pork, beef or chicken.
Apply barbecue sauce for about the last 10 minutes.
If meat gets a little black around the edges, it's not the meat burning, it's merely the sauce getting black.

title: carolina cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
In small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: basic brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa.
Remove from burner and add sugar.
Beat well with spoon.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well and add chopped nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in Crisco.
Place in shallow greased baking dish. Sprinkle celery, brown sugar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour sauce and water over chops.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until chops are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deluxe taco dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork or blender.
Mix avocado, sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Season to taste with red pepper and Tabasco.
Spread bean dip across the serving platter.
Spread mix from avocado mix over bean dip.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese (sharp).
Add grated Monterey Jack pepper cheese.
Cover with chopped tomatoes.
Cover with chopped green onions.
Finally, add chopped black olives.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, which have been well beaten.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Add with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon into 10-inch tube pan or one large enough for 12 cups.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: no sugar chocolate ice cream(serves 4)
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, mash bananas.
Melt chocolate with water, either in microwave or top of double boiler.
Add melted chocolate and water to bananas, stir and freeze before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: jovita's pumpkin piewarren, texas
directions: In a large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: christmas morning souffle
directions: Brown sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard and sausage. Stir in cheese.
Pour
over bread cubes.
Refrigerate overnight (absolutely necessary) in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: chocolate truffle pie
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese, and butter in microwave safe bowl.
Melt on 100% power for 30 seconds, then stir.
Repeat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, triple sec and powdered sugar. Pour into pie shell.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Spoon sliced strawberries on top of pie and top with whipped toppings.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in greased casserole.
Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry cheese crumbs
directions: Melt margarine, mix together margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Cream these and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool this.

title: american casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Place half of noodles in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Brown beef.
Combine with tomato sauce. Combine next 5 ingredients.
Place on noodles.
Add rest of noodles.
Top with sauce.
Pour butter over top.
Place in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Prepare broccoli by cutting and using only the tops.
Fry, drain and crumble the bacon.
Sliver the onion; add raisins.

title: lasagna primavera
directions: Drain and set aside noodles.
Mix Ricotta with Parmesan, spinach and eggs.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of large 10 x 15-inch lasagna pan.
Top with a layer of cooked noodles, then a thin layer of Ricotta mixture and layer of peas. Scatter sliced Mozzarella over vegetables and spread a layer of sauce.
Repeat layers lasagna, Ricotta, another vegetable, Mozzarella and sauce.
Finish with noodle layer.
Spread sauce over top and sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, then 30 minutes uncovered at 350°.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: gorp
directions: Mix and eat.
Use as topping for oatmeal.

title: fruit cheese cake dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in refrigerator until time to use. Cut fresh fruit to serve with dip, such as strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew, etc.

title: settler's bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Fry hamburger with onion.
Crumble bacon and add to hamburger and onion mixture.
Place in casserole.
Add butter beans, kidney beans and pork and beans with all their water.
Add white sugar, brown sugar, ketchup, mustard, molasses and salt. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes, uncovered.

title: "the night before" breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13 x 2 inch casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: autumn spice punch
directions: Make syrup of first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add chilled juices, ginger ale and ice.

title: everlasting applesauce muffins
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nuts and vanilla.
Add flour and applesauce alternately.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Batter will keep in covered container in refrigerator for 6 weeks.)

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: In mixing bowl, combine peas, cauliflower, celery and onions. In small mixing bowl, blend salad dressing (or mayonnaise) with sour cream.
Pour over vegetable mixture; toss to coat.
Stir in pecans; sprinkle bacon on top.
Refrigerate.

title: clam chowder(12 servings)
directions: Melt butter in 6 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Add half and half, cream soups and clams.
Cook on low for 6 hours.

title: hamburger-carrot casserole
directions: Combine meat, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pat meat in bottom of a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of onions, then carrots, ending with potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water until smooth.
Pour evenly over meat and vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper, onion and celery.
Mix rest of things together and add to meat mixture.
Simmer for awhile.

title: hardening dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until the mixture is stiff.
Cool the dough.
Knead until smooth.
Shape as desired.
Store in an airtight container.
The clay will harden overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup and seasonings and 1/2 of onions.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish; top with cheese and then pour remainder of bean mixture on top of cheese.
Sprinkle top with other 1/2 of onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Let stand for 20 to 25 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: taco bean dip
directions: In skillet, brown the ground chuck, that has been seasoned with the taco seasoning mix to taste (I use about 2/3 of package).

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and wash the potatoes, then dice and cook until tender. Drain potatoes and place in a large bowl.
Chop the celery and onion in small pieces.
Dice pickles.
Place celery, onion and pickles in
the potatoes.

title: chicken licking good pork chops
directions: Mix flour, salt, mustard and garlic powder together in bag. Place chops one at a time in bag and flip around.
In skillet, brown chops in 2 Tbsp. oil.
Place in slow cooker.
Pour in chicken and rice soup.
Cover and cook on low 6-8 hours.

title: crock-pot meat balls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Roll into small balls, brown in skillet until done.
Place meat balls in crock-pot.
Add soup and Worcestershire sauce and turn to coat meat balls.
Cook in crock-pot until desired doneness.

title: chicago italian beef
directions: Place all ingredients in roaster pan.
Cover roaster and bake in oven at 250° for about 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender. Baste and turn meat several times during cooking.
Take out of oven and cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook cabbage in salted water, uncovered, until fork-tender.
Drain off water and place cabbage in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crush entire package of chips then line casserole dish with 1/2 of chips.
Next place all of tuna on top first layer of chips and top with
remaining chips.
Mix soup and 1/2 can milk well and pour on top of all layers.
Heat in microwave for about 10 minutes or until heated completely.

title: herbed steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and brush all over steak. Salt and pepper. Refrigerate at least 5 hours; no longer than 24 hours. Cook at 250° for 3 hours.

title: hot wassail
directions: Stick 4 small oranges with cloves. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Heat spices and cider.
Add cinnamon sticks and bring to a boil.
Put in bowl to serve.
Put oranges in to float.

title: halibut with hazelnut crust
directions: Cut apple in half and core.
Chop 1/2; reserve other 1/2 for garnish.
In small skillet over medium-low heat, heat olive oil and add chopped apple.
Cook 1 minute, then add shallots and sugar. Continue cooking until apple is tender, 1 minute.
Add lemon juice and remove from heat.
Cool, then puree in blender until smooth. Pour pureed mixture into bowl.
Add the Dijon then slowly whisk in the oil.
Add the 1 teaspoon lemon zest, 1/2 teaspoon thyme and season with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pinch of cayenne pepper.
Stir in the water.
Cut the remaining 1/2 apple into 1/4-inch dices. Toss with dressing; refrigerate.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Slowly add milk, beaten egg and vegetable oil and mix well; set aside.
Coat a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with additional vegetable oil and place in preheated oven for approximately 10 to 15 minutes (oil should start to smoke).
Remove the skillet and pour in batter.
Reduce oven heat to 400° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove bread from oven and brown under a broiler.
Turn out onto an ovenproof plate and serve hot with melted butter.

title: egg custard
directions: Blend the milk with water and pour over slightly beaten eggs. Add salt.
Pour in an unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with desired amount of nutmeg.
Place in a pan filled with hot water while baking.
Bake at 300° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: nutty-chocolate-thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream
the
first 5 ingredients in small bowl.	Combine flour, cocoa
and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Chill 1 hour
or until firm enough to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg
white
slightly.
Dip
each
ball
into egg white.
Roll
in nuts.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press thumb gently in center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10
to 12 minutes and remove from pan gently.
Press kisses or cherries in center of each cookie.
Cool.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Trim the cutlets, flatten them lightly with a cutlet bat, and with a sharp knife make nicks round the edges so that they will not curl up when cooking.
Dip the cutlets into the beaten eggs and then coat them with breadcrumbs, pressing them well into the meat to form an even coating.

title: mother's shortcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and save out 1/2 cup.
Add milk and butter; mix until blended.
(It will be lumpy.) Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup dry mixture over top of the cake and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken risatto
directions: Brown chicken pieces in half of the margarine; when browned, take out and set aside.
Add rest of margarine, garlic and rice; brown slightly.
Add broth and cook until liquid is absorbed.
Put chicken pieces back in pan and warm.
When served, put cheese on top.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine margarine and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda and spices.
Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: baked tomatoes and corn
directions: Simmer tomatoes about 5 minutes.
Add corn, green pepper, onion, butter and pepper and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Place alternate layers of vegetable mixture and bread crumbs in greased baking dish, ending with a layer of crumbs.
Dot with unsalted butter and bake in a hot oven (400°) about 20 minutes or until browned.

title: peanut haystacks
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels together in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add noodles and peanuts to mixture and mix well until coated.
Form little clusters on foil and set in refrigerator to harden.
Makes 24 haystacks.

title: french onion burgers
directions: Shape beef into 4 patties 1/2-inch thick.
Cook patties in skillet until browned.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, heat to boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Top with cheese.
Serve on rolls with soup mixture for dipping.

title: velma's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain, mash and add remaining ingredients, adding sour cream last.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp with apples and snow peas
directions: Cook peas in
boiling
water until tender-crisp; plunge in cold water.
Reserve.
In
large skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute apple
slices
until
mushy.
Sprinkle
with sugar and turn up heat to brown.
Remove and reserve.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and add 1/4 pound grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Season meat, add onion	and
press
into a flat greased baking dish.
Add hot
tomato
soup,
undiluted.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
(You can substitute cream of mushroom or celery soup, if you desire.)

title: chicken a la king casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain and set aside.
Saute celery, pepper and onion.
Mix soup, milk and salt, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add to noodles, pour all into a buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs (crush saltine crackers and mix with 2 tablespoons melted butter).
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix 3 or 4 minutes, then add chips by hand and fold in.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: dieter's delight salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese in bowl.
Stir to mix well. Add pineapple, oranges and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 4 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk and cheese.
Sprinkel chicken with flour and seasonings, then dip in buttermilk mixture coating both sides and using entire mixture.
Dip chicken into crumbs, turning to coat both sides.
In small nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken. Cook, turning once until done.
Serves 1.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, eggs and baking soda. Stir in pineapple. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cake layers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat for 2 to 4 minutes.
Pour into 6 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350°.
Time is short!
Watch closely.

title: mocha ice cream dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 1/3 cup butter and press into bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Then spoon softened ice cream over crust and freeze until ice cream is hard.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in oblong pan, greased, about 13 x 9 x 2-inch size.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown, about 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: beth's bran muffins
directions: Mix shortening and boiling water.
Add eggs, sugar and salt. Mix and cool.
In a bowl mix flour, buttermilk, soda and Bran Buds.
Mix everything together.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all together and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Great with barbecue and large groups.

title: three minute pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pudding in a cone
directions: Mix up 2 packages of pudding as directed on package. When it has set, spoon it into ice cream cones and eat.
Makes 16.

title: lemon pie(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Pour condensed milk into a large bowl. Fold in the Cool Whip, mixing very well. Add lemon juice and stir well. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Chill for 2 hours and serve.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce for veggies
directions: May use any of your favorite vegetables to toss with the sauce.
Chill.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls, and mix well. Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Spoon 1/2 cup of mixture onto center of each rectangle. Seal and brush top with 1 tablespoon melted margarine. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers crosswise, about 4 or 5 slices per inch. Cover with white lime dissolved in 2 gallons of water.
Soak for 2 hours.
Rinse well.
Cover with clean, cold water.
Soak for 2 hours.
Drain, then add the sugar, cloves and mixed spices tied in bag, salt and vinegar.
Let stand overnight in this solution (use container you cook them in).
In the morning, put on stove and boil 35 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Melt butter in frying pan and place chicken in hot butter. Cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Turn chicken over and add artichokes and mushrooms.
Then, add sherry, chicken stock, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Cook until sauce becomes a creamy consistency and add green onions.
Serve.

title: double yellow cake
directions: Cream together until fluffy in large mixing bowl the shortening, margarine and sugar.
Beat in thoroughly the eggs. Stir in flour alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Serve with Pineapple Filling and Double Boiler Frosting.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix salt, flour and powder.
Add Crisco with knife, cutting in.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Drop onto chicken and broth or beef stew.
Cover closely and steam 15 to 20 minutes, then remove cover.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt half the butter in large skillet or heavy bottomed pot. Prepare veggies.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and seasonings. Saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Combine clam juice and liquid from canned clams.
(Yields 2 cups.)
Add to mixture and cook over medium heat.

title: crockpot pork country style
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. Put pork pieces into crockpot; pour mixture over top. Top with onion slices. Cook 8 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown chili meat and drain well.
Add all ingredients and let cook for 15 minutes.
Season to taste.
Add bay leaves last.
Let simmer about 2 or 3 hours, stirring every once in a while.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Shape into 20 meatballs.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Or, place in an ungreased baking pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs and rind.
Sift flour before measuring.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to first mixture. Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven about 15 minutes. While still warm, spread with frosting.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat over low temperature until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: white corn salad
directions: Drain corn and green beans. Set aside. Chop celery, bell pepper and green onions and mix with corn and green beans. Blend vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in saucepan and bring to boil. Set aside and let cool.

title: skillet upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 3/4 cup butter in a heavy 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle the brown sugar and strawberry gelatin over butter.

Drain the crushed pineapple over gelatin mixture. Prepare cake mix according to directions on package, using reserved pineapple juice plus water to measure 1 1/3 cups liquid. Pour cake batter over pineapple mixture.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Immediately turn Upside-Down Cake onto a serving dish.

title: lemon cake dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle jello over mixture and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Combine pecans and coconut; sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Yields 15 servings.

title: old fashion macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package; drain well. Layer 1/3 of macaroni in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat procedure and top with remaining macaroni (reserve remaining cheese).

title: chocolate soda
directions: Mix chocolate sauce and club soda.
Add ice cream.
Fill glass with club soda.

title: pasta with spring vegetables
directions: Prepare vegetables and place in top of steamer.
In a kettle, cook garlic and pepper flakes in oil, over low heat, stirring until the garlic is softened.
Add tomatoes and boil, stirring, for 5 minutes or until thickened to a puree.
Stir in basil and salt and pepper to taste.

title: quiche madeleine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute peppers in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add diced onions.
Saute until clear.
Add chopped up meat.
Stir until meat is softened.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, milk and water together.
Add salt, whit pepper, nutmeg and parsley flakes.
Fold cut pieces of cheeses into mixture.
Add onions, peppers and meat.
Stir all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour mixture into two 9-inch pie shells (deep dish).
Place in oven for 45 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting a knife in the center. If it comes out clean, it's done.
Glory!

title: kraut salad
directions: Chop peppers and celery into small pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: condensed squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pack into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Store covered. Cut into 25 squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well by hand, will be thick.
Roll into small balls (your desired size).
Place on cookie sheet; press down with fork.
Keep putting fork in water so dough won't stick to fork.
Cook at 250° until brown, 10 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Wash peppers and halve.
Remove ribs and seeds.
Cut lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Scrub zucchini and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices. Wash eggplant.
Cut lengthwise into quarters, then into 1/4-inch slices.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sweet potatoes, butter, sugar and soda.
Mix with buttermilk until desired consistency.
Roll and cut.
Bake a 400 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to directions on box.
Mix vegetables together.
Mix cheeses, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef. Add water; simmer until tender. Add water as necessary while cooking. Add mushrooms (include juice) and beef base. Thicken broth.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover bottom with bread slices.
Cover with slices of Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with onion.
Cook and crumble the sausage; drain and cool a bit and layer over the onion.
Sprinkle sausage with grated cheese (as much as you like).
Put bread cubes on top of sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight and/or beat eggs with milk and mustard.
Add salt and pepper and pour over the casserole.
Let set for 1 hour. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Great served with blueberry muffins.

title: festive flamed cherries
directions: Scoop ice cream into serving dishes.
Heat pie filling and spoon over ice cream.
Soak sugar cubes in rum or rum extract; place on cherries and ignite.
Makes a quick and easy festive dessert.

title: parmesan cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Shape on serving board to resemble pine cone and garnish with almonds or pecans.

title: waffles
directions: Put package of yeast in the warm water.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar.
Add the yeast mixture.
Add oil.
Add sifted flour, alternating with warm milk, until all is incorporated.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken with asparagus
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken with flour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, heat salad oil.
Cook chicken pieces until light brown.
Mix cheese, wine, chicken soup, salt and pepper in dish.
Put chicken in mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: drip beef
directions: Put all ingredients (except water and roast) in cheese cloth with ends tied to form a small bundle of spices.
Place roast in crock-pot and pour water over it.
Put spice bundle on top of roast.
Cook on low all day.
