Serve on buns; dip in juice. Wonderful.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken and vegetables with lemon juice.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Combine cake mix and instant pudding.
In a separate bowl, add sour cream, oil, Kahlua, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add cake mixture and mix together thoroughly.
Mix in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: saucy cheese bits
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Can be frozen.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown onion, celery and garlic in stew pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook at low boil for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs.
Add garlic salt, ginger and pineapple juice. Simmer until half soft.
Remove ribs and refrigerate separately overnight.
Remove solidified fat from liquid.
Combine ribs and liquid in pot.
Add shoyu, vinegar and brown sugar.
Season with salt, pepper and ajinomoto.
Thicken sauce if desired.

title: reese's chocolate
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in heavy pan on medium heat. Stir in vanilla. Mix well.
Slowly add sifted confectioners sugar. Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate chips and Paregin.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper to dry.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Brown hamburger with chili seasoning.
Add tomatoes and kidney beans; cook for approximately 15 minutes.
Add refried beans, mixing well.
Cook about 3 minutes and set aside.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine orange slices, dates, nuts and coconut with 1/2 cup flour and salt.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine soda and milk.
Add alternately with flour; beat well.
Add orange slices, dates, coconut and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Turn into 1 large or 2 small well-greased and floured tube pans.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together; drop in hot oil and fry until brown.

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in muffin tins for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: creamy fruit soup
directions: Thaw and drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Cut up strawberries, if whole.
In medium saucepan, combine reserved syrup, 1 cup water, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Blend 1 tablespoon water with cornstarch.
Stir into syrup mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice. Cool to room temperature.
Blend in sour cream and fruit.
Stir in milk.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with strips of lemon peel, if desired.

title: refried beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Cook them in cold water.
Add salt later.
Cook until real done and tender.
Drain and mash.

title: fall apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients except the last two.
Wash and slice apples; dip in orange juice.
Drain.
Arrange in circle on a pretty plate and place dip in center in a bowl.
Sprinkle additional chopped peanuts on top of dip.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: wuzbree
directions: Wash the meat, salt and dust with caraway seed.
Place fat side up (this can be scored in little squares, if desired) in your roasting pan.
Add a little water, cover and place in a 350° oven. After an hour or so, turn and return to the oven, uncovered, and bake until the skin is red and the meat is tender.
Roasting time depends mostly on the quality and size of the roast.
Allow on the average about 30 minutes to the pound.
Baste frequently with the dripping from the pan.

title: louisiana cornbread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Top with glaze.

title: serbian cabbage
directions: Fry a few slices in butter.
Top with cheese slices, leaving in the pan until cheese is melted.

title: banana pudding
directions: Let cream cheese soften. Follow the directions on the pudding box. Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese with the pudding. In bowl, layer vanilla wafers and bananas. Top with half of the pudding mixture. Add second layer of wafers and bananas and top with the remaining half of the pudding.

title: dippin' bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cut bagels into bite size pieces.
Jump in and enjoy out of this world taste.

title: snik snak
directions: Put cereals, noodles, peanuts and pretzels in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix melted butter and seasonings.
Pour over cereals and stir.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes, stirring and turning dish every 2 minutes.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: In heavy 12-inch skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter and 1/4 cup oil over moderate heat.
Add onions and cook, turning frequently, for 10 minutes or until they are soft and lightly browned.

Stir in peppers; reduce heat, cover and cook 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, vinegar, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 5 minutes. Cook vegetables, uncovered, over high heat, stirring gently, until most of liquid has boiled away.
Reseason.
Serve at room temperature.

title: white chocolate chip macadamia cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
In large bowl beat together butter, granulated and brown sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in white chocolate chip and nuts.
Drop by tsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350 for 8-10 minutes.

title: grilled marinated wing-dings
directions: In large bowl combine the white wine, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, pineapple juice and honey.
Add wings to sauce mixture, turning to coat.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Reserve the marinade to use for basting while grilling wings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Cook all ingredients together in water until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: old troller crab dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let sit overnight or several hours. Serve with Captain's Wafers.

title: apple slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise and marshmallow creme and pour over cabbage mixture.
Add pecans.
Toss and serve.
Great with spaghetti.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook celery, onion and garlic in butter or margarine until tender.
In separate pan, brown Italian sausage.
In separate pan boil shrimp.
In separate pan prepare rice.
Add to vegetables the undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice, sausage and shrimp to tomato mixture.
Season to taste.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape and cut carrots into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in boiling water until done.
Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Place a layer of carrots in 2-quart Pyrex casserole and cover with layer of onion, bell pepper and portion of sauce. Repeat.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, then remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for about an hour.
Test with toothpick to see if done.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Combine beaten egg and water.
Add to mix, stirring until blended.
Bake in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips and margarine.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
On 3 pieces of wax paper, place a strip of coconut about 3 inches wide and 10 inches long.
Drop 1/3 of the mixture on each of the prepared wax paper.
Form into logs. Refrigerate, then cut into slices.
Enjoy!

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and apples.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased pie pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sliced pickles
directions: Combine cukes and salt.
Let set for 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dredge tomatoes in flour or cornmeal mixed with salt, pepper and sugar.
Shake.
Fry in
hot oil, turning only once.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients together; add carrots and stir gently.

title: bogie's ribs
directions: First you will need a barbecue pit where the fire is at one end and not
under
the
meat.
Start your fire with charcoal, then add red oak
wood
as you need it to cook the ribs. Buy as many racks of
ribs as you need or have room for on the pit. Generously cover
ribs
on
each
side with garlic salt, pepper, chili powder and brown sugar.
Let ribs cook one hour; sprinkle with more brown
sugar
and turn over.
Cook one hour more, then sprinkle more brown sugar on and turn back over and cook for another
hour
or
until
desired degree of doneness. These are finger-licking good!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together salsa, Sweet 'N Low and hamburger meat.
Cream potatoes as usual.
Layer casserole with potatoes, then hamburger meat, then potatoes, etc.
(potatoes on top layer).
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: country macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
Add to combined salad dressing and dill weed.
Mix lightly.
Add chicken, carrots and tomatoes.
Mix lightly. Chill 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce covered plate. Garnish with fresh dill weed.

title: ciambelle (from gaeta)(white frosted cookies)
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients.

title: beef and tater bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Make layer of uncooked beef in a 9-inch square dish. Cover with onions; add a layer of tater tots. Add chicken soup (pouring evenly over mixture). Bake 45 minutes then top with cheese and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Heat milk and cream cheese; blend well.
Stir 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and green pepper into milk mixture.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Stuff into 6 peppers that have been cored and seeded.
Cover and boil in 1 1/2 inches salted water for 30 minutes.

title: arkansas hot cheese dip
directions: Cook in double boiler, adding ingredients in order given, except egg.
Cook 20 minutes.
When almost ready, remove from fire and add beaten egg.
Serve in chafing dish with toast points or tortilla chips.

title: shrimp gumbo(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add all ingredients, except shrimp; mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook for 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: "cornflake oatmeal cookies"
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cornflakes) together, form into small balls and roll in crushed cornflakes.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Set oven to 350°.
Mix together in small bowl and set aside the apples, 4 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
In large bowl mix together other ingredients.
Arrange the batter and apple mixture in layers.
Begin with batter and end with apples, 3 layers of each.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours (for Teflon pan bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or two 6-cup Bundt pans for 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: potato soup
directions: Slowly cook bacon and drain.
Meanwhile, peel and dice onion and celery.
Cook onion and celery (covered with water).
Peel and cube potatoes.
Add to celery mixture.
Again cover with water and add salt.
When celery and onions are tender (potatoes will be mushy) add milk and heat slowly.
Do not boil!
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mom's strawberry shortcake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs on medium speed for 3 minutes. Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until thick and lemon-colored. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Beat into egg mixture. Heat the milk and butter just until butter begins to melt. Beat into batter with vanilla (batter will be thin). Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for at least 10 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix together next 5 ingredients and then add yeast mixture.
Add enough of the flour for a good dough.
Put in greased pans and let rise and bake or store in refrigerator for later use.

title: cranberry orange salad for 50
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food chopper.
Add sugar. Pour boiling water on gelatin; stir until thoroughly dissolved. Chill only until cold.
Add relish.
Pour into lightly oiled square or rectangular pans.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Serves 50 people.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Melt stick of margarine and saute bell pepper and onion. Combine chicken, soups, sauteed pepper and onion and Ro-Tel in a large mixing bowl.
Add Doritos and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: no fat fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Pour 1 cup of juice into pudding mix.
Stir and cook on High in microwave until thickens.
Take out and add pineapple and oranges.
Chill in refrigerator.
Then add cherries and bananas.
Stir all together and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto oiled cookie sheet. Dip bottom of glass in sugar and mash down. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mrs. raines yeast rolls
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add boiling water and cool. Dissolve yeast in cold water and add first mixture. Add eggs which have been beaten stiff. Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Shape in muffin tins and let rise for 2 hours. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in chopped egg, parsley, onion, and garlic.
Chill until serving.
Serve with vegetables.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together, then pour into a greased and floured 8-inch rectangular baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon wads(chess cake squares)
directions: Combine softened oleo and egg, then add cake mix.
Press this in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together the softened cream cheese and 2 eggs; gradually add powdered sugar.
Pour over first layer. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: In bowl, combine meat, crumbs, egg and 2 teaspoons bouillon; shape in 1 1/4-inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs. Remove from pan; pour off fat.
In skillet, combine preserves, ReaLemon brand and remaining 2 teaspoons bouillon.
Over low heat, cook and stir 15 minutes.
Add meatballs; simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli, bacon cheddar toss
directions: Combine first four ingredients and next 3 ingredients in separate bowls.
Mix first bowl with second.
Toss.
Add bacon, crumbled, just a few minutes before serving.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sweetener, vanilla and egg on high speed.
Add flour, water, soda and cinnamon and beat until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.

title: christmas banana spice nut bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oleo, sugar, vanilla and bananas.
Slowly add flour, baking soda and spices.
Add nuts last.
Bake in greased and floured pan of choice (Bundt, bread or other pan) at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dust meat with flour and pepper.
In a skillet, brown the meat in butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in soup.
Cover and cook 1 hour, stirring often.
Gradually blend in sour cream.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Always add sour cream the last 5 minutes, never more.

title: peanut butter fruit drops
directions: In a bowl, beat together the peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Stir in eggs, honey and milk until well blended.
Stir in candied fruits and peels.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually blend into candied fruit mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove and cool.

title: cajun chops
directions: Gently	cook
pork
chops
in Worcestershire sauce in a nonstick skillet.
Sprinkle front and back of chops with Cajun spice,
salt
and
pepper.	Cook over low to medium heat.
Add Worcestershire
sauce
as
needed, as it will evaporate during cooking.
Cook until golden brown.

title: roast beef party logs
directions: In a large bowl, combine the ground roast, steak sauce, celery, relish and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Shape into logs about 5 to 6 inches long.
Refrigerate. In another bowl, cream together the cheeses.
Add the onions, pimiento and bell pepper.
Mix well. Spread this mixture over the logs. I like to use my hands for this.
It might be a little difficult and messy but it is worth the trouble. An easy way to keep from getting the cream cheese mixture all over your hands is to use a plastic sandwich bag on your hand.
Sprinkle each log with paprika and roll it in the chopped pecans.
Yield: about 12 logs.

title: petite cherry cheese cakes
directions: Beat cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line muffin pans with liners and put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill each 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top each with 1 tablespoon pie filling.
Chill.

title: crispy oven fried fish(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Using 1 teaspoon vegetable oil, grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in plastic bag or shallow dish.
Combine first 7 ingredients.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add cut up chicken.
Mix soup and chicken broth together and pour over chicken.
Drain liquid from vegetables and spread over chicken and soup.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water. Let stand 2 hours or more; drain, rinse and drain thoroughly. Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in large saucepot. Bring to a boil. Add the drained vegetables; simmer for 10 minutes. Pack hot relish into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps and seal. Makes approximately 8 half pints.

title: brown jug cheese soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven mix the first 4 ingredients (bouillon cubes, water, onions and celery).
Cook over medium heat until onions and celery are tender.
Add potatoes and vegetables.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add soup and cheese (cut in chunks).
Stir constantly so cheese does not stick.
The soup is ready to serve when the cheese is melted.
Freezes well.

title: italian slaw dressing
directions: Mix dressing well and pour over shredded cabbage, carrots, onions and green peppers.
Toss well.
Cover bowl with lid tightly and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: macaroni and tomato soup
directions: Crumble hamburg into frypan. Dice onion and add to hamburg. Cook on medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes until done.
Drain grease. Add Worcestershire sauce to hamburg and let set.

title: marie's chicken fried rice
directions: Cook and refrigerate rice.
(Warm rice gets mushy!
I usually cook mine the day before.)
Saute onions lightly.
Put in dish and set aside.
Scramble eggs.
Put in dish and set aside.
Have bean sprouts ready to add, if desired.
Dice chicken, cook in water and season to taste (salt, pepper, seasoned salt, lite soy sauce). When chicken is done, add onions, eggs, bean sprouts and rice. Stir.
Add soy sauce.
When rice is hot, dish is done.

title: meal in one
directions: Steam vegetables.
Brown hamburg in skillet; add vegetables and soup.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: alex kalberer's aspen spinach
directions: Grease square oven dish with oleo.
Drain marinade from artichokes and put marinade into frying pan.
Cut artichoke hearts in 1/2 or 1/3 and put into dish.
Saute mushrooms slightly in marinade until tender.
Put mushrooms in dish; salt and pepper. Put spinach layer on next.
Mix cream cheese and milk until icing consistency.
Spread over spinach.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until golden and slightly bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.

title: chicken with vegetables
directions: Cook chicken; bone.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add vegetables, soup and broth.
Mix.
Add butter.
Mix Bisquick and milk; pour on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream oleo, sugar and sugar Twin at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add egg whites and vanilla. Beat on medium for 1 minute. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add water to creamed mixture along with the flour mixture; mix for 1 minute until smooth. Add chips to dough and mix lightly. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets that have been lined with foil or are nonstick.
Press down with fingers dipped in cold water; form circles, about 2 inches in size. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown. Yields 44 cookies.

title: honey cake
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in the coffee. Beat the eggs and add sugar and honey.
Add dry ingredients.
Also add the raisins and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chewy date nut bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix and brown sugar.
Add butter and eggs; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine dates and walnuts; stir into batter (the batter will be stiff). Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Run a knife around sides of pan to loosen; cool completely before cutting.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Brown onion in bacon fat.
Mix brown sugar, catsup and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Layer sauerkraut and onion until all in casserole pan.
Pour sauce over top and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: date cake
directions: Pour water and soda over chopped dates. Add sugar, flour, butter and nut meats to date mixture. Mix well. Add eggs. Mix well.

title: tuna sensation
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
One half hour before serving, remove from refrigerator and let mixture stand at room temperature so that the mixture will be of dipping consistency.

title: squash casserole
directions: Make cornbread and bake.
Cut up squash and onion in pan and cook these two together until very tender.
Drain the water off of squash, then mash very well.
Can put into food processor.
Mix this together with cornbread, beaten eggs, cream of chicken soup and other ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 to 50 minutes until top is brown.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Wash grapes; dry.
Dice water chestnuts.
Mix with chicken; add celery, grapes and 2 cups almonds.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon, curry and soy sauce.
Combine with chicken mixture and chill for several hours in large glass or steel bowl.
Place serving on lettuce leaf; sprinkle each with reserved cup of almonds and pineapple chunks.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg with strawberries and shortening.
Sift all dry ingredients into strawberry mixture; stir until just moistened.
Add chopped nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes in pan before putting on rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Use 9-inch lightly greased quiche dish or deep pie pan. Bring water and salt to boil.
Stir in grits.
Cook 30 minutes or until done.
Remove
from
heat and add next 3 ingredients. Stir until cheese is
melted.	Gradually
stir
hot grits into eggs; add remaining
grits;
stir well.
Pour grits into quiche dish. Bake at
350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with mushroom and parsley.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Put pie filling on top of pie.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: broccoli-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Slice top off each tomato; scoop out pulp with a small spoon.
Invert tomato shells on paper towels to drain.
Spoon broccoli mixture into tomato shells.
Serve warm or chilled.
Yields 6 1/2 dozen.

title: wendy's frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on medium speed until creamy.
Stir if necessary.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and flour. Beat on high for 10 minutes.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water until soupy.
Add garlic cheese and margarine.
Add eggs and milk.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and paprika and return to the oven to brown for 10 minutes more.

title: jellied tomato juice aspic
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Pour over contents of package of gelatin.
Stir well; place in refrigerator.
Allow to set until firm.

title: aunt zulma's orange cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salt water, then drain.
While potatoes are still warm, mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate until cold.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with juice. Combine dry ingredients; cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and brown meat.
Saute onion with meat.
Add squash and meat mixture in casserole dish.
Add egg and crackers and mix.
Add cheese on top.
Cook for 25 minutes in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: sausage stuffing(for turkey)
directions: Soak the bread in water for about 1/2 hour.
Next, mix all prepared ingredients together, making sure the bread was well distributed with the other ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Stuff turkey and close skin.
Bake as usual.
Makes enough stuffing for a 12 to 16 pound turkey.
Use a sage-flavored sausage for an extra flavor.
This stuffing will help keep the turkey moist from the inside.
Cut the recipe down to stuff a roasting hen or other bird.
Any stuffing that will not fit inside the bird can be baked in a casserole until hot all the way through.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Place sugar and Karo syrup in a pan and bring to boil.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups of peanut butter and pour over 6 cups of Special K cereal.
Put in a pan after mixed together.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Let this harden at room temperature approximately 1 hour.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Blend well the sugar, eggs and oil.
Add milk and vanilla. Gradually blend in flour; mix well.
Add walnuts.
Bake in 3 round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine pancake mix and water.
Bake on properly heated griddle.
For thicker pancakes, use less water.
For thinner pancakes, use a little more water.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Place the cabbage in a heavy enameled pot with the water, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper; cover pot and cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Add the sugar and apples; cook another 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add the butter and red wine. Excellent with Danish Pork Roast.
Serves 6.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: In a large bowl layer 1/2 of first 6 ingredients in order given; cover with 1 cup mayonnaise mixed with sugar.
Repeat layers in order.
Do not mix.
Cover with remainder of mayo/sugar. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before you serve.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour in saucepan.
Add milk, bread crumbs and egg yolks.
Thicken like custard and add to flaked salmon.
Pour into buttered pudding dish and fold in whites of eggs, beaten stiff.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat oleo and Crisco until fluffy; gradually add brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle a little flour over nuts; add nuts to batter.
Line tube pan with wax paper or grease and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: good times butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour three 8 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Beat on low speed until smooth.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pat shrimp dry with paper towels; set aside.
Melt butter in frypan over medium heat.
Stir in green onion, oil, garlic, lemon juice and salt; cook until bubbly.
Add shrimp to pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turns pink (4 to 5 minutes). Stir in parsley, lemon peel and hot pepper seasoning.
Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake as directed on package.
For icing, mix sugar, milk and vanilla until sugar melts.
Add peanut butter and cook until thickens.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken with almond rice
directions: Brown chicken slowly in butter.
Heat broth, instant minced onions and undrained mushrooms to boiling.
Add uncooked rice and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the dry
cake mix with the jello mix.
Add oil, milk and eggs,
one at a time.
Add strawberries (coconut and pecans).
Beat well.
Bake	in
3 to 4 (9-inch) layer pans or one (9 x 13-inch) layer pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 1, 2, 3 dumplins
directions: Boil chicken; drain and cool. Heat soup and water over medium heat. Tear apart chicken and tortilla shells into medium sized pieces. Add to soup and cook until the tortilla shells "puff up" (about 15 minutes). Salt and pepper to taste. Quick and delicious!

title: boiled chocolate cookies (with peanut butter)(no bake)
directions: Mix together and boil for 1 1/2 minutes the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk with pinch of salt.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, cereal and vanilla.
Stir well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and they will become firm and ready to eat.

title: mock eggnog
directions: Combine milk, egg substitute, sugar/substitute and extracts in blender.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir before serving.
Sprinkle with ground nutmeg.
Makes two 8 ounce servings.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Press ingredients in pan. Bake until golden brown (about 20 minutes at 350°). Set out and let cool completely.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut up candied fruits, dates and nuts.
Use white raisins whole.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks of eggs.
Sift together 4 cups flour with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add this to creamed mixture alternately with fruit juice and dissolved soda in buttermilk.
Use the remaining 2 cups of flour to dredge the fruit and nuts.
Pour batter over fruit mixture and mix.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 275°.

title: corn dodgers
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add egg and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into very hot, deep cooking oil.
When Dodgers rise to top and are browned to suit you, they are done.

title: mexican ice cream sundaes
directions: Top ice cream with chocolate syrup; sprinkle with ground cinnamon and sunflower seeds.

title: cream chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix in saucepan, 1/2 cup sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until scalded.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir half the mixture into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it begins to boil.
Immediately remove from heat. Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool.
When mixture is partially set, beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Blend in vanilla; gently fold in whipped cream.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar; when slightly stiff, add sugar and fold in cream mixture.
Pour into ready made baked crust.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.
Chill.

title: kid's ice cream
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs, brown sugar and peanut butter with an electric mixer on low speed until blended.
Stir in whipping cream, chocolate covered peanuts, melted milk balls and milk.
Freeze in a 4 or 5-quart ice cream freezer according to the manufacturer's directions.
Serve with hot fudge sauce. Makes about 1 1/4 quarts ice cream.

title: breakfast sausage, eggs and cheese
directions: Crumble sausage and cook until brown.
Mix milk, Bisquick, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper with sausage.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gene burris' pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour 3 pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring sugar and cherries to a boil. Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of water.
Add to cherries and sugar.
Then add nuts and pineapple (juice and all).
Add orange juice.
Refrigerate.

title: tropical champagne punch
directions: Combine Hawaiian Punch and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add brandy and chill.
When ready to serve, add champagne.
Add ice and serve.
Garnish with oranges and strawberries.
Yields 10 (8 ounce) servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, combine 1 stick margarine and cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix eggs, 1 stick margarine and powdered sugar. Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes (very important).
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with sliced bananas.
Cover bananas with drained pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and dot with cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt.
Heat until very hot.
Place cucumbers in jars along with dill seed, peppers and garlic.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers and seal using hot flats.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix together; pour into cookie sheet and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: cornell barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together using a blender or egg beater.
Pour over chicken and marinate for several hours.
Great cooked on a grill.

title: ham
directions: First boil ham in water. Cover ham with mustard and vinegar for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Then take Coke and brown sugar and make a paste with it. Rub this all over the ham (the more the better). Now put in foil-wrapped pan in oven for about 3 hours at 350° to 400°. Pour about 16 ounces of Coke to baste with. Cover and baste often. When the Coke is thickening up, your ham should be done.

title: dirty rice
directions: Lightly brown sausage in large frying pan.
Chop vegetables and add to sausage.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and stir until vegetables are tender, approximately 15 minutes.

title: bettie's chicken pot pie
directions: Line pan with chicken.
Mix soups, broth and veggies together. Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and butter together.
Pour over chicken evenly.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour until brown. Makes 10 servings.

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: Place beef in 2-quart glass measure or bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
Stir in beans, seasonings mix and 1 cup water.
Cook on High 5 minutes, stirring once.
Pour sauce into pie plate.
Dip both sides of tortillas in sauce. Layer beef mixture and tortillas in microwave-safe 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, cutting tortillas as necessary to fit.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Cook on Medium-high 10 minutes, turning dish once.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and black olives, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in medium, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Chill until firm.
Very good.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into 9 x 16-inch greased pan. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans. Blend all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute while constantly scraping the bowl. Beat on medium speed for 1 minute. Pour into pans. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour or until wooden toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pans. Rub each loaf completely with margarine or butter. Cool completely before slicing.

title: master pie mix
directions: Start with 1/3 cup cold water for 2 cups of mix and add more, if needed.
Two cups of mix will make 1 double crust pie.
This is enough for approximately 24 single pie crusts and may be stored on the kitchen shelf in 2 Tupperware Econo canisters.

title: easy meat and potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
In ungreased 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish evenly layer potato slices.
In small bowl combine flour, salt and pepper; sprinkle over potato slices.
Spoon ground beef over potatoes and spoon vegetable soup evenly over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Uncover and sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Makes four 1 1/2-cup servings.
